subject: Prepare for a coding interview in Python
body:
Hi there,

We have 10 new courses covering Python, R, and SQL. Take our unique Preparing for Coding Interview Questions in Python course and gain confidence with coding-based questions that you would encounter in a technical coding interview.

For SAS users, gain a gentle introduction to the R language with every chapter of our R for SAS Users course providing a detailed mapping of R functions to SAS procedures, highlighting similarities and differences. We’re also launching one new coding challenge, Intermediate R for Finance.

Finally, check out five courses that are top-rated by other DataCamp users.

body:
Dear Google group owner or manager,

We’re writing to let you know about changes we’re making to the settings  
experience of Google Groups.

In response to your feedback, we’re updating the Groups’ settings  
experience starting May 6, 2019. The goal is to make it easier for you to  
manage and configure your groups.

****** About these changes ******

- We’re removing some rarely-used settings and features, and we’re  
combining similar settings. Learn more about the settings changes:  
https://support.google.com/a/answer/9191148

- We’ll start rolling out these changes on May 6, 2019, though you might  
not see changes until May 21, 2019.

- When the changes take effect, we’ll automatically update the settings for  
existing groups to map to the new experience.

- These updates may affect how you manage your groups.


****** Important notes **********

- Some group members may lose access to group management features:  
Depending on your current settings, some group members who currently can  
access specific group management features may lose that access. To make  
sure group members have the right access, you may want to audit your groups  
and adjust the settings before May 6, 2019.

- Settings for groups you currently own or manage will be updated to match  
the new settings. Note: You can change your group settings at any point.

- Groups you create after May 6th will have the new settings by default.

- We recommend you audit your groups settings after the changes to confirm  
your groups are set up the way you want.

- If you need help, visit our Help Center:  
https://support.google.com/a/answer/9191148


Sincerely,

The Google Groups Team

==========================================================================================


© 2019 Google LLC. 1600 Amphitheatre Parkway, Mountain View, CA 94043

We sent this to alert you to important changes we’re making to your Google  
Groups settings.
label: Updates

subject: Important updates to Data Studio
body:
Data Studio is migrating your files. No action is needed. You'll be able to  
keep using Data Studio the same way you are today, with the same sharing  
and real-time collaboration features you're used to.




Google



September 2019




Data Studio is migrating your files

Since its initial release, Data Studio has used Google Drive to store and  
share reports, data sources, and explorations. To enable a number of  
product improvements, and to enable users without Drive to use Data Studio,  
we will be migrating all Data Studio files away from Drive.

You do not need to take any action.

You'll be able to keep using Data Studio the same way you are today, with  
the same sharing and real-time collaboration features you're used to.



• For non-G Suite users, your existing Data Studio files will be migrated  
in the next few weeks. Anyone who currently has access to reports or data  
sources you've created will continue to have access.

• For G Suite users, your Data Studio files will not be migrated yet. G  
Suite admins will receive further instructions about how to migrate their  
users.



Once the migration is completed, files you have created in Data Studio will  
no longer be accessible through Google Drive. This change will facilitate  
product improvements, like better search, a simplified process for  
connecting to data, and improved admin and file management capabilities. If  
you've been using Drive to organize your Data Studio reports, you'll soon  
be able to do this directly in Data Studio.

To ensure a seamless migration, we've also simplified the way data sources  
work with your credentials. When you create a data source with Owner's  
credentials, that data source will be able to retrieve data using your  
credentials until you choose otherwise.

We're adding the ability to revoke your credentials from data sources you  
have created if you no longer want those data sources to use your  
credentials. You can revoke your credentials from an individual data  
source, or you can revoke your credentials from all data sources you no  
longer have access to.

Thank you,

The Google Data Studio Team







Google

© 2019 Google LLC 1600 Amphitheatre Parkway, Mountain View, CA 94043

You have received this mandatory email service announcement to update you  
about important changes to the Data Studio product.

*Machine Learning is the science of getting computers to act without being
explicitly programmed. In the past decade, machine learning has given us

subject: Invite for SANKALAN'19
body:
Greetings!
The dates have rolled again and the time is ripe to announce the most
awaited and celebrated event of DEPARTMENT OF COMPUTER SCIENCE.: SANKALAN '
2019
scheduled from 09/03/2019 to 10/03/2019 (Saturday-Sunday).
SANKALAN'19 is reloaded.
This time more quirky, more technical, more fun, more food and more
memories.

We hereby, solicit your presence to embrace  the occasion and add glint
with your words and experience .

-- 
Regards
Sankalan Panel 2019
DUCS

Subject: Fwd: Approximation notes : Please Keep the corrections mentioned
by Ma'am in mind
To: <mcs17du@googlegroups.com>, Khushboo Mittal <khushboomittal87@gmail.com>



---------- Forwarded message ----------
From: Ayush Malik <ayush.mcs17.du@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, Nov 23, 2017 at 5:08 PM
Subject: Approximation notes : Please Keep the corrections mentioned by
Ma'am in mind
To: Eva Chaudhary <eva.mcs17.du@gmail.com>


Analysis of 2 factor VC:

1. We don't need any sophisticated algo like EK for Maximal M...simple
iterative algorithm is sufficient....but its ok since we have not discussed
any other algorithm for maximal M in the class....just a comment
2. Construction of V' from MM is not constant....


2 factor for TSP

1. I suggest you people revise the algorithm to construct an ET in a given
graph, see the name of its author and see its time complexity. Mention this
while discussing the time complexity of the algorithm.....If you want, you
can write to me and get it verified.....Refer to some book on discrete
structures

2. While saying cost(TSP) <= Cost(ET) by triangle inequality, it will be
better to show with the help of an example figure.

3. 3/2 factor for TSP

1. Claim1 cannot be skipped for exam. Its very important.
2. Page 5...last line: reason in bracket ( M is min weight perfect matching
in H and M1 and M2 are perfect matchings in H)
3. Good...that you have written Hungarian Algorithm for Min weight perfect
matching....similarly do for ET also.

Rest is good.

All the best. Please forward on the group.

Neelima

--

subject: Re: New foodie on Zomato | Megha Sundriyal
body:
Hi Megha,

Welcome to Zomato. Here are a few tips for you to get the most out of Zomato –

Order food online –

Tap ‘order food online’ on the home screen of your app to order food without calling the restaurant. Over 1.5 crore orders get placed through Zomato app every month. Here’s why.

  • Deepest discounts (up to 40% off) from thousands of restaurants
  • Widest choice of restaurants ~ 2x of any other food ordering app
  • Fastest delivery service in the country – with live order tracking
  • 7500+ top rated restaurants are exclusively available on Zomato to order food

Trusted restaurant ratings –

Always check the Zomato rating of a restaurant before going to or ordering from a new place to avoid disappointment. Our ratings come from hundreds of thousands of people who write genuine reviews about their food experiences at restaurants.

Zomato Gold –

Buy the exclusive Zomato Gold membership, which is now available in your city. The Zomato Gold membership helps you discover great new places in your city without burning a hole in your pocket (you get 1+1 on food, and 2+2 on drinks on hundreds of top rated restaurants)

---

I really hope you enjoy your time on Zomato. On the slightest whim, please feel free to reach out to me by replying to this email. I would love to hear your experiences and feedback.

And thank you for joining us on the mission of building the first large global consumer brand out of India. Your feedback and loyalty will go a long way to help us make you proud of us.

Cheers!
Deepinder
Founder & CEO, Zomato

subject: Panel Elections 2019
body:
Hello Juniors,

The date for the Panel Elections has been finalized.
It will be conducted on Monday, 18th February 2019 at 1:00 pm

The elections will be preceded by a small meeting with NK Sir.
All the students in the first year are expected to be present in the
meeting.

Note to CRs - In case your classes clash with scheduled election timing,
you are encouraged to sort this matter out at your level. Request the
teachers for re-scheduling or cancellation of classes, whichever is
suitable.

It is to be noted that only those students who have contributed to the
sankalan fund will be allowed to take part in the elections.
Those who have not contributed will be discarded from nominations and their
votes will not be counted.


-- 
Regards
Sankalan Panel 2019
DUCS

subject: Donation for CRPF
body:
As we all know, last week, a deadly terrorist attack by a Jaish-E-Mohammad
terrorist killed 40 Indian *Central Reserve Police Force (CRPF)* personnel
and injured several others. At this time, various government and
non-government organizations, as well as individuals, have come forward to
help the families of the Pulwama attack martyrs.
The least we can do to help is create a monetary fund for the families of
those who laid down their lives in the line of duty.

If anybody from the Department wishes to contribute any amount, howsoever
small, they can do so by:
i) Visiting https://bharatkeveer.gov.in/, an initiative by the Ministry of
Home Affairs, or
ii) contribute the donation to *Jayant Dhawan, *via Google Pay, PayTm or
PhonePe on *8950253252, *or on his UPI id *jayantdhawan@dbs *(remember to
mention "Bharat ke Veer" in the purpose/comments while paying)

The donations done to *Jayant Dhawan *will be collected and sent as a
combined contribution from The Department of Computer Science to *"Bharat
ke Veer".*

*Thank you.*

-- 
You received this message because you are subscribed to the Google Groups "DU MCS18" group.
To unsubscribe from this group and stop receiving emails from it, send an email to mcs18du+unsubscribe@googlegroups.com.
To post to this group, send email to mcs18du@googlegroups.com.
To view this discussion on the web visit https://groups.google.com/d/msgid/mcs18du/CAP5LJ0g%3DBQ3RiPuecNJOzM1tZcxJa%2BaZ8oEjzuu5s24g%3DUN-Pw%40mail.gmail.com.
For more options, visit https://groups.google.com/d/optout.

A Radical Guide to Spending Less Time on Your Phone (https://medium.com/@RyanHoliday/a-radical-guide-to-spending-less-time-on-your-phone-a5419b1538ee?source=email-7bc7ce57268a-1568065329138-digest.reader------0-49------------------ddaeab85_2b8a_4595_8a66_b9cee159b167-1-----&sectionName=top)

11 min read

subject: Workshop - Sankalan Portal & Web Development
body:
Hello guys!

This year, we used an online portal for Sankalan. I wanted to share my
knowledge with all the students, how I built this portal from scratch.

The idea is to share everything related to this portal, from code,
database, frameworks, testing to the deployment. I want to cover each and
every single part of the development process. So, It can be a day workshop,
as there is a lot to cover.

I request everyone of you to please fill out the form given below and let
me know whether you are interested or not, and share your ideas.

👉 Share your thoughts here.
<https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScco_UbFeyfkvGLCqWMKG0Fhp3pglC2ox2ltXuVXkTVNXXYsQ/viewform?usp=sf_link>

Thank you.

Regards,
Ruman Saleem
MSC 1st year (2018-2020)

With Google Groups you can invite anyone to join your group using their  
email address. Know who you want in your group already? You can skip the  
invite and directly add up to 10 people at a time.

Share Google Docs and Calendars directly with your group
Working with shared documents and calendars has never been easier than with  
Google Groups. Share your files with the group directly and access will  
update whenever someone is added or removed from the group.

Get organized
Google Groups has several options for organizing content in your discussion  
group including: categories, tags, and tracking topic resolutions.

subject: Welcome to Google Data Studio
body:
Google Data_studio





Beautiful reporting is just a few steps away

Hello megha,

Welcome to Google Data Studio! You're about to create stunning data  
visualizations, insightful reports, and intuitive, easy-to-use dashboards.


CREATE A REPORT





Here's how to get started:

• Connect to your data — Our data connectors make it easy to bring together  
the data you need to create interactive dashboards and dynamic reports.

• Find inspiration in our template gallery — Not a designer? No problem.  
Explore our gallery of reports and dashboard examples. If you see something  
you like, make a copy and connect your data.

• Share your reports — Working together, gathering feedback, and sharing  
results has never been more convenient.



The Data Studio Help Center also has a wealth of articles, videos, and more  
to guide you along the way.




Happy reporting,
The Google Data Studio Team

subject: K-means clustering
body:
Two methods are used for determining the optimal clusters, which includes:
1. Elbow method
2. Silhouette method

The total within-cluster sum of square measures the compactness (i.e
goodness) of the clustering and we want it to be as small as possible.

subject: Agenda for Placement Class on 07-02-19
body:
Greetings!

An hour-wise agenda for the upcoming placement session has been attached.

*Timings: 09:00AM to 06:00PM*

i) The mentor has requested everyone to reach the department by *08:45AM. *

ii) He said that the basic introduction from *09:00AM to 09:30AM *will be
important and should not be missed.

iii) He also said that if the students do not revise the topics mentioned
in the previous mail, he will have to spend more time on basic concepts and
questions, and may not have time for discussing advanced problems asked in
major companies. So, everyone is required to thoroughly go through the
topics mentioned and practice pen-paper based coding for the same so that
the mentor may cover advanced topics as well.

*All are expected to come on time.*

*Placement Coordinators 2019-2020*

-- 
You received this message because you are subscribed to the Google Groups "DU MCS18" group.
To unsubscribe from this group and stop receiving emails from it, send an email to mcs18du+unsubscribe@googlegroups.com.
To post to this group, send email to mcs18du@googlegroups.com.

subject:
Fwd: Formation of IEEE student branch in the Department of Computer
 Science, University of Delhi
body:
Regards
Office
Department of Computer Science
University of Delhi
Delhi-110007


---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: priyanka rathee <rathee.priyanka124@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, Aug 27, 2019 at 3:01 PM
Subject: Formation of IEEE student branch in the Department of Computer
Science, University of Delhi
To: himani saini <office.cs.du@gmail.com>


Dear students

We are planning to start IEEE student branch in our department i.e. in the
Department of computer science, University of Delhi.

A Student Branch provides opportunities to meet and learn from fellow IEEE
student members and engage with professional IEEE members locally. An
active IEEE Student Branch can be one of the most positive elements at a
college or university offering programs, activities, and professional
networking opportunities.

*Faculty and department support, as well as signatures of at least 12
active IEEE student members are needed for a Student Branch petition**.*

*The benefits of student branch are given in the document as attached.*



For more information, please feel free to contact

Dr Priyanka, Assistant Professor, Department of Computer Science.


Thanks & Regards

*Dr. Priyanka Rathee*
*Chairperson*
*IEEE Young Professionals,*
* Delhi Section*

*Assistant Professor*

*Department of Computer Science *

*(Faculty of Mathematical Sciences)*

*1st Floor, New Academic Block *

*University of Delhi *

*Delhi - 110007. India.*


*Find me on linkedin here: *www.linkedin.com/in/priyanka-rathee-31066667

---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: Sana from Galvanize <galvanize@entrayn.com>
Date: Wed, Jan 23, 2019 at 8:38 AM
Subject: Dear Prof. Vasudha Bhatnagar,, your students are invited. Last
chance to participate in the GRE Olympiad!
To: Prof. Vasudha Bhatnagar, <vasudhabhatnagar@gmail.com>




Dear Prof. Vasudha Bhatnagar,

We’re reaching out to you again because you have to know this..

We’re thrilled to let you know that on the *27th January 2019*, *Galvanize
Test Prep* is holding our most popular event  - *the Online GRE
Olympiad. *Galvanize
Test Prep are the makers of the highest-rated GRE prep apps in the
world. *Currently,
students from over 190+ countries prep for the GRE exam with us.*

We know this* Online GRE Olympiad will make a big difference to those
students of your institution who want to study abroad. *This event will
help them clear any doubts they might have about the process. And, it’s
completely *free to attend. *

We request you to share the below emailer with the students so that they
could grab this big opportunity.

Thanking you in advance.

Team Galvanize


*Subject: Online GRE Olympiad | How GRE-ready are you compared to
test-takers across the globe? *





<http://sendy.entrayn.com/l/XTCzJquAeLXOJBXrGbf1AA/hekUkoN6NaoOBocCuKIRbw/1gmvIirHHKaay11OhHRDQA>




*Dear Student,*

I’m thrilled to announce that this January, everybody’s favourite *Online
GRE Olympiad* is back!
If you dream of *studying abroad and winning a scholarship*, you* cannot
miss this event. *Compete with *100,000 students* from *1500+ colleges* all
over the world to see where you stand. And, it’s absolutely free.

*Register now for better GRE Scores. It only takes one click.
<http://sendy.entrayn.com/l/XTCzJquAeLXOJBXrGbf1AA/K9763AiZ763Uju763jrmcVPezUdg/1gmvIirHHKaay11OhHRDQA>*

Galvanize is pleased to invite you and your friends to participate in
the *ONLINE
GRE OLYMPIAD* on *Sunday, 27th January 2019 *to help identify your
capabilities & assess your potential to compete with GRE test-takers across
the globe.
*Sunday,  27th January, 2019*
*11:00 AM - 06:00 PM (IST)*
*REGISTER NOW*
<http://sendy.entrayn.com/l/XTCzJquAeLXOJBXrGbf1AA/K9763AiZ763Uju763jrmcVPezUdg/1gmvIirHHKaay11OhHRDQA>
*or Log-on to www.gxprep.com/Olympaid
<http://sendy.entrayn.com/l/XTCzJquAeLXOJBXrGbf1AA/5F9fMBlLl0SPQDrkC330Iw/1gmvIirHHKaay11OhHRDQA>*
*Test duration: 30 mins. To avoid disappointments, make sure you register
asap.*

*But that’s not all. Win exclusive GRE prizes to improve your score and get
a dream admit + scholarship.  *

   -

   GRE Real-feel. Know where you stand across the nation/globe
   -

   Premium GRE Videos.
   -

   Exclusive Scholarships on GRE prep courses.
   -

   Personalized feedback to get you on the right track.
   -

   Expert GRE Counseling & Profile Evaluation

*No hassle, you only have to click a button and register. *
*Click Here
<http://sendy.entrayn.com/l/XTCzJquAeLXOJBXrGbf1AA/MiXqOe763mAzFTOf8892tX3Vew/1gmvIirHHKaay11OhHRDQA>,*
to
be a volunteer for this GRE Olympiad and get exciting gifts!

*Cheers!*

*Team Galvanize. Helpline: +91 97910 55035*
*www.GalvanizeTestPrep.com*
<http://sendy.entrayn.com/l/XTCzJquAeLXOJBXrGbf1AA/xNkb4sLlFPQpuQ35Qlhakg/1gmvIirHHKaay11OhHRDQA>

subject: Fwd: Invitation for OnLoad Hackathon
body:
Regards
Office
Department of Computer Science
University of Delhi
Delhi-110007


---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: Vasudha Bhatnagar <vbhatnagar@cs.du.ac.in>
Date: Tue, Feb 19, 2019 at 10:01 PM
Subject: Fwd: Invitation for OnLoad Hackathon
To: office cs du <office.cs.du@gmail.com>
Cc: Sapna Varshney <svarshney@cs.du.ac.in>


Please forward to CRs
Thanks
VB

------------------------------
*From: *"OnLoad Hackathon" <contact@hackonload.com>
*To: *"vbhatnagar" <vbhatnagar@cs.du.ac.in>
*Sent: *Tuesday, February 19, 2019 4:12:35 PM
*Subject: *Invitation for OnLoad Hackathon

We the team behind  "OnLoad Hackathon" feels privileged to invite students
of you esteemed institute to attend the event.

OnLoad is a 30hrs intense, fun-filled, rewarding convergence of young
talented programmers, designers, and developers from all over the country
working together, to build something amazing.

They will work on the cutting edge technologies including but not limited
to Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, Blockchain, IOT, and many
more leveraging available tools and APIs creating new tools towards the
common goal of creating a better world.

This hackathon is happening in Mysuru, the Palace City of India on March
23rd-24th.

Further information is available on our website https://hackonload.com

To make this event greater we request support from you. Please share this
event with your students. Your students will get utmost benefits and
opportunity to learn and develop new skills by attending the event. We
would appreciate if our event invitation reaches each student of your
institution from your side and get a fruitful reaction and lot more
participation from your institution.

Your promising hands will make this event a grand success.
label: Personal

[image: Google Forms]
TWO-DAY WORKSHOP on CYBER SECURITY & CYBER LAWS (25th Mar – 26th Mar 2019)
<https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSf7U6vwfhcaEgyvKmTM_a459GcYTOLZB8OcqjU1dmKqtxG_BA/viewform?vc=0&c=0&w=1&usp=mail_form_link>
The advent of technology in the last decade has been immense. It has
integrated into our lives deeply and unavoidably. And while technology has
already brought many beneficial changes, it can be argued that it also has
a dark side – that of cyber-attacks. In this digital age, we should know
how to protect ourselves, our privacy, identity and sensitive information
from cyber-attacks. Therefore, getting familiar with cyber security
fundamentals is the way to go in today’s interconnected environment.
The purpose of this workshop is to provide an introduction on the practices
and challenges in cyber security; emerging threats and trends in cyberspace
and technological challenges that are posed by the rising threats in
cyberspace. It will also provide an opportunity to learn about the current
state of Cyber security and Laws in India.

Our Experts
1. Mr. Surender Kumar Verma, Scientist ‘C’
Indian Computer Emergency Response Team
Ministry of Electronics and IT
Topic: BotNet Detection Methodologies
2. Mr. Dhanajoy Dey, Scientist ‘F’
Scientist Analysis Group, DRDO
Topic: Introduction to Quantum and Post Quantum Cryptography
3. Dr. Anurag Jain, Associate Prof.,
USICT, GGSIPU
Topic: CyberPAD- Case study of plastic card fraud
4. Inspr. Sajjan Singh
Topic : Cyber Forensic
5. Mr. Rahul Tyagi, Vice President,
Lucideus Tech pvt. Ltd
Topic: Securing Digital India from Cyber Attacks
6. Mr. Neeraj Aarora, Senior Advocate,
Supreme Court of India
Topic: Admissibility and authenticity of electronic evidence
7. Mr. Akash Jain, Cyber Law Head,
Lucideus pvt. Ltd
Topic: Legal Regime of Cyber Crime

The workshop is organized by Department of Computer Science, University of
Delhi in collaboration with ICSL and SSCBS.

Venue of workshop: Seminar Hall, Shaheed Sukhdev College of Business
Studies (SSCBS), Dr. K.N. Katju Marg Rohini Sector 16, PSP Area IV, New
Delhi, Delhi-110089

Fill out form
<https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSf7U6vwfhcaEgyvKmTM_a459GcYTOLZB8OcqjU1dmKqtxG_BA/viewform?vc=0&c=0&w=1&usp=mail_form_link>
Create your own Google Form
<https://docs.google.com/forms?usp=mail_form_link>

subject: Session for our students will be held on 12.11.18 @ 2.00PM
body:
*              सूचना*

*NOTICE*



Session for our students as per the details given below will be held as per
the following schedule:





Presentation 1

Sudhanshu Vishnoi of MCA Sem V will present his work on GSoC-2018 Project
titled 'Implementing cross references and general improvements in ReSpec'
for Mozilla to implement new features, fix some existing issues and improve
maintainability of the ReSpec project.



Presentation 2

The Zoo Hackathon Team ‘Error: Error not Found’ (Runner-up position) will
present their work on Alexa voice-based skill 'Wildlife Guru' that provide
details about the wildlife products, wildlife species in trade, laws, list
of organizations that can be contacted to report a crime, etc.





Day & Date

*: Monday**, November 12th , 2018*

Time

*: 2.00 PM*

Venue
: Seminar Room, 1st Floor   Department of Computer Science   New Academic
Block   University of Delhi   Delhi – 110007




All are cordially invited.
Regards
Office
Department of Computer Science
University of Delhi
Delhi-110007

subject: Amazon Campus Mentorship Series
body:
Greetings!

This mail is regarding Amazon Campus Mentorship Series(ACMS) 2019-20.

*Reporting time - 09:30AM*

*Date of Launch and Test-*
23th November, 2018

*Details of PPT and Test-*
Launch - 09:30AM to 11:00AM
Test - 11:00AM to 12:30PM
Platform - Hackerearth (familiarise yourself with interface before
appearing for test)

*Pattern of Test-*
i) 20 MCQ questions
ii) 2 coding questions
iii) Personality based question
Duration of test - 90 minutes

*Dress code-*
Decent attire, formals not compulsory

*Resume-*
You will be required to upload resume during registration tomorrow.

*Detailed process as explained by Amazon representative-*
1. All interested female students will attend a PPT & test on 23rd Nov.
2. Students shortlisted from this test will be a part of ACMS program and
attend sessions for 4-5 weeks.
3. At the end of ACMS, they will make a PPT and attend a test. Everyone
shortlisted here will attend onsite interview and get an internship offer
if they clear the interview. Finally selected candidates will not be
allowed to sit for regular campus placement of Amazon.
4. All those who do not clear the PPT, test or interview post ACMS can sit
for regular campus placement.

*Placement Coordinators 2019-2020*

subject: What is Data Science?
body:
"Data science" can be hard to define, and the definition is constantly evolving. We thought it would be helfpul to share a working definition since you're just getting started with us.

 

DataCamp ( https://www.datacamp.com )

 

 

---------------------
What is Data Science?
---------------------

 

Learn the entire data science workflow ( https://www.datacamp.com )

 

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Data Science is the interdisciplinary process of importing, cleaning, manipulating, modeling, and visualizing data.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

At DataCamp, you will use Python ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/tech:python ), R ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/tech:r ), SQL ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/tech:sql ), and Spreadsheets ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/tech:spreadsheets ) to explore all aspects of data science, using techniques from computer science, mathematics, statistics, and more.

Did you know:

•

Data science is used in nearly every discipline, including business, healthcare, law, engineering, and more.

•

There is currently a huge demand for qualified data scientists.

•

"Data Scientist" was ranked the best job in America in 2016.

•

The average salary for data science positions is over $100,000.

Learn Data Science by Doing ( https://www.datacamp.com )

subject: Prepare for a statistics interview in Python
body:
Hi there,

We have eight new courses covering Python, R, and SQL. Take our new Preparing for Statistics Interview Questions in Python course and learn how to master classic interview concepts ranging from conditional probabilities, to A/B testing, to the bias-variance tradeoff, and much more!

Learn how to structure your PostgreSQL to run in a fraction of the time in our Improving Query Performance in PostgreSQL course. We’re also launching one new coding challenge, Introduction to Time Series Analysis in Python.

Finally, check out five courses that are top-rated by other DataCamp users.

Courses

•

Improving Query Performance in PostgreSQL ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/improving-query-performance-in-postgresql?utm_medium=email&utm_source=customerio&utm_campaign=course_16324 )

•

Preparing for Statistics Interview Questions in Python ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/preparing-for-statistics-interview-questions-in-python?utm_medium=email&utm_source=customerio&utm_campaign=course_16463 )

•

Working with Geospatial Data in Python ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/working-with-geospatial-data-in-python?utm_medium=email&utm_source=customerio&utm_campaign=course_7356 )

•

Deep Learning with PyTorch ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/deep-learning-with-pytorch?utm_medium=email&utm_source=customerio&utm_campaign=course_15510 ) (in Python)

•

Sentiment Analysis in Python ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/sentiment-analysis-in-python?utm_medium=email&utm_source=customerio&utm_campaign=course_16852 )

•

Ensemble Methods in Python ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/ensemble-methods-in-python?utm_medium=email&utm_source=customerio&utm_campaign=course_15296 )

•

Business Process Analytics in R ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/business-process-analytics-in-r?utm_medium=email&utm_source=customerio&utm_campaign=course_6004 )

•

Probability Puzzles in R ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/probability-puzzles-in-r?utm_medium=email&utm_source=customerio&utm_campaign=course_11371 )

Coding Challenges

•

Introduction to Time Series Analysis in Python ( https://datacamp.app.link/DhMvAJonqP/?course_id=4267 )

5 Courses recommended by DataCamp users

•

Improving Query Performance in SQL Server ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/improving-query-performance-in-sql-server?utm_medium=email&utm_source=customerio&utm_campaign=course_15222 )

•

Forecasting Using ARIMA Models in Python ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/forecasting-using-arima-models-in-python?utm_medium=email&utm_source=customerio&utm_campaign=course_17329 )

•

Streamlined Data Ingestion with pandas ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/streamlined-data-ingestion-with-pandas?utm_medium=email&utm_source=customerio&utm_campaign=course_16719 ) (in Python)

•

Object-Oriented Programming in Python ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/object-oriented-programming-in-python?utm_medium=email&utm_source=customerio&utm_campaign=course_10071 )

•

Natural Language Processing Fundamentals in Python ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/natural-language-processing-fundamentals-in-python?utm_medium=email&utm_source=customerio&utm_campaign=course_3629 )

Happy learning,

The DataCamp Team

subject: Placement Meeting
body:
Greetings

You are hereby informed that a *Placement *G*uidance meeting *and your
*Placement
Coordinator Elections* will be held *between *26 October 2018 and 31
October 2018.

Tentative Dates :
*Guidance Meeting : 26 October 2018*
*Elections : 30 October 2018*

The timings will be informed before hand ( 2 - 4 hours ) and the guidance
meeting will surely end before 5:00 p.m.
The reason behind immediate timings is that the availability of 2 sections
and the placement coordinators need to be considered.

After the first meeting the interested candidates can submit their names
for the post of placement coordinators.

*All the students of the concerned classes have to be present from 26
October 2018 to 31 October 2018 ( except Saturday and Sunday ).*

*Instructions :*

   - *The students who don't turn up for any 1 or both of the meetings will
   not be allowed to stand for the post of placement coordinator*.
   - Don't come up with excuses or means of digital presence ( including
   video calls, messages, etc ).
   - Only your physical presence in the room at the time of the meetings
   will make you eligible to ask doubts.
   - Absentees will not be entertained.
   - On the day of voting, you have to present in the room at the time of
   voting.Turning up slips, proxies, informing your friends about your
   favorite candidate or other such means will be discarded.
   - Don't take these instructions lightly.


Our very best wishes to all !
Regards
*Placement Coordinators 2018-2019*

--

DataCamp ( https://www.datacamp.com )

-------------------------------------------------

A Data Scientist combines statistical and machine learning techniques with Python programming to analyze and interpret complex data.

subject: Srijan'19 Panel Selection
body:
Srijan’19

Annual Tech Magazine of Department of Computer Science


Greetings to you all,

With a new academic year, DUCS is all set to offer you new opportunities.
The Opportunity to pursue your creativity and be a part of something
bigger!  We are here with yet another facet of this department, Srijan, the
annual tech magazine of DUCS.

The Srijan Panel currently consists of 4 members:

Editors -

Jatin Rohilla - MCA 2nd year
( jatin.mca17.du@gmail.com )

Ashita Diwan - MSc. 2nd year
( ashita.mcs17.du@gmail.com )

Designers -

Vipin Kumar - MCA 2nd year
( vipin.mca17.du@gmail.com )

Shreshth Saxena - MSc. 2nd year
( shreshth.mcs17.du@gmail.com )

Every year on Sankalan, the annual technical fest of DUCS, we release a new
edition of Srijan, the annual tech magazine of DUCS. This year will
continue the legacy and take it even further.

We are looking for a responsible, creative and dedicated team to lead and
work with us on this new edition of Srijan. So, If you are one of those who
looks for constructive recreation, join Srijan.

The selection process for the Srijan 2019 Panel is explained in the
attachment. Kindly go through it, and do as needed before the deadline. The
recent edition of Srijan is also attached in the mail. Please go through it
for reference. For previous editions, feel free to check out our website
https://www.ducs.in/srijan/

Srijan'18 : https://bit.ly/2CtRAKJ

Deadline : 21st January 2019

For any queries, drop a message to any of the panelists. You can also reach
us at  ducs-srijan-2019@googlegroups.com, ducs.srijan@gmail.com

All the Best!

PFA : *Selection Process 2019.pdf*

body:
Today's highlights

Choosing the Right Metric for Evaluating Machine Learning Models - Part 2 (https://medium.com/@aswalin/choosing-the-right-metric-for-evaluating-machine-learning-models-part-2-86d5649a5428?source=email-7bc7ce57268a-1569881783740-digest.reader------0-59------------------aebdc202_2e5d_4e5c_94d3_5dd5fc9018e7-1-----&sectionName=top)

Second part of the series focussing on classification metrics
Alvira Swalin (https://medium.com/@aswalin?source=email-7bc7ce57268a-1569881783740-digest.reader-------------------------aebdc202_2e5d_4e5c_94d3_5dd5fc9018e7)
 in USF-Data Science (https://medium.com/usf-msds?source=email-7bc7ce57268a-1569881783740-digest.reader-------------------------aebdc202_2e5d_4e5c_94d3_5dd5fc9018e7)
8 min read


Logistic Regression Model Tuning with scikit-learn - Part 1 (https://medium.com/@finnqiao/logistic-regression-model-tuning-with-scikit-learn-part-1-425142e01af5?source=email-7bc7ce57268a-1569881783740-digest.reader------1-59------------------aebdc202_2e5d_4e5c_94d3_5dd5fc9018e7-1-----&sectionName=top)

Comparison of metrics along the model tuning process
Finn Qiao (https://medium.com/@finnqiao?source=email-7bc7ce57268a-1569881783740-digest.reader-------------------------aebdc202_2e5d_4e5c_94d3_5dd5fc9018e7)
 in Towards Data Science (https://medium.com/towards-data-science?source=email-7bc7ce57268a-1569881783740-digest.reader-------------------------aebdc202_2e5d_4e5c_94d3_5dd5fc9018e7)
7 min read


A Beginner's Guide to Installing Jupyter Notebook Using Anaconda Distribution (https://medium.com/@neuralnets/beginners-quick-guide-for-handling-issues-launching-jupyter-notebook-for-python-using-anaconda-8be3d57a209b?source=email-7bc7ce57268a-1569881783740-digest.reader------2-59------------------aebdc202_2e5d_4e5c_94d3_5dd5fc9018e7-1-----&sectionName=top)

subject: Collection
body:
Hello Juniors,

We hope you all are doing well. As said earlier, we collect amount of Rs
1,000 for organizing Sankalan event. We have till date received very less
amount from you all. Hoping that you all will contribute soon, so that we
can plan and manage accordingly.

So, please do contribute the said amount and hand it over to your
respective class CR's as soon as possible.

Hope to see a better response in next couple of days.

We will be very thankful to you all.


Regards,

Sankalan Panel 2019
University of Delhi

Sapna Varshney.

wrote:

> Dear All,
> Pls refer to the attached document for installing software for Deep
> Learning workshop.
> The hands on session may be conducted online as well...in that case
> installation will not be required.
> However, you are advised to come prepared with the required softwares
> installed on your systems in case the need arises.
>
>
> ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
> FOR ONLINE HANDS ON SESSION-
> Google Colab provides pre-installed online Python libraries with both CPU
> and GPU support up to 12 hrs of free usage.
> Google Colab can be accessed using Google drive. It provides a the
> following specs:
>
> GPU: 1xTesla K80 , compute 3.7, having 2496 CUDA cores , 12GB GDDR5 VRAM
>
> CPU: 1xsingle core hyper threaded Xeon Processors @2.3Ghz i.e(1 core, 2
> threads)
>
> RAM: ~12.6 GB Available
>
> Disk: ~33 GB Available
>
> Feb/2019 Update: GPU instance upgraded to 319 GB free space
> https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/welcome.ipynb#recent=true
>
> Here are some links to explain how to use Google Colab with Google drive :
>
>

>
>
> https://towardsdatascience.com/getting-started-with-google-colab-f2fff97f594c
>
>
> -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

> University of Delhi, Delhi
>

A Brand New Trello View Welcome to Trello! 
  
View in Browser → 
<https://i.trellomail.com/e/evib?_t=cce9a87967214196ae72b08c7283fda9&_m=9f1d031ec600444fb951afcb7d930e07&_e=UK-665EMenJ0ZYR9c4JvolsOFZGtvmkcP2gMEr73aP5uEtl-kaNoY2kR4zKj4xhIGju-SW8R0gtJpPYn7Mbe-45hDgqgleHruz9CCiXt_CDJuLlJ2bhaXq5YWnlJqhQj>
 
<https://trello.com?utm_source=lifecycle&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=trello-welcomeSolo>



Hey megha, 

We’re so happy you’re here! The concept is simple: Trello helps you get 
organized, get motivated, and get more done (with your team or on your own).

Go To My Boards → 
<https://trello.com?utm_source=lifecycle&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=trello-welcomeSolo>
Here are the most popular resources to help you get started:



 * Guide to Getting Started with Trello 
<https://trello.com/guide?utm_source=lifecycle&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=trello-welcomeSolo>
 * Team Playbooks 
<https://trello.com/teams?utm_source=lifecycle&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=trello-welcomeSolo>
 * Get the Trello Mobile App 
<https://trello.com/platforms?utm_source=lifecycle&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=trello-welcomeSolo>


Going forward, you’ll receive our bi-monthly newsletter (which is chock full 
of Trello best practices and sample workflows, as well as productivity hacks). 
Separately, you’ll also get notification emails based on activity within 
Trello. You can adjust the frequencyhere 
<https://help.trello.com/article/793-receiving-trello-notifications?utm_source=lifecycle&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=trello-welcomeSolo>
.

That’s it, all you need to get started with Trello, and if you’re ever feeling 
stuck, you can always contactTrello Support 
<https://trello.com/contact?utm_source=lifecycle&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=trello-welcomeSolo>
 ☺.

Thanks! We're excited to have you on board,
 The Trello Team

Thank you for registering to the Hindustan Unilever BFS Datathon by
Unilever!

now. *Once you have a team in place, you need to solve the qualifier round
challenge to get shortlisted for the final round.*

<https://skillenza.com/challenge/hul-bfs-datathon/checkpoint?utm_source=checkpoint&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=unilever>*

the entire team.

*Team formation Last Date: *September 1st 2019, 11:55 pm, IST
*Qualifier Data Science Challenge Last date: *September 2nd 2019, 3:00 am,
IST

Kindly ignore this email, if you have already done.

body:
Today's highlights

Lambda, Map, and Filter in Python (https://medium.com/@happymishra66/lambda-map-and-filter-in-python-4935f248593?source=email-7bc7ce57268a-1568496906514-digest.reader------0-59------------------bba676a2_8097_406c_b264_28c5cb1da4f0-1-----&sectionName=top)

A look at the syntax and usage of each function
Rupesh Mishra (https://medium.com/@happymishra66?source=email-7bc7ce57268a-1568496906514-digest.reader-------------------------bba676a2_8097_406c_b264_28c5cb1da4f0)
 in Better Programming (https://medium.com/better-programming?source=email-7bc7ce57268a-1568496906514-digest.reader-------------------------bba676a2_8097_406c_b264_28c5cb1da4f0)
3 min read


Python Data Science Getting Started Tutorial: NLTK (https://medium.com/@swayammittal65_2667/python-data-science-getting-started-tutorial-nltk-2d8842fedfdd?source=email-7bc7ce57268a-1568496906514-digest.reader------1-59------------------bba676a2_8097_406c_b264_28c5cb1da4f0-1-----&sectionName=top)

I. Analyze words and sentences using NLTK
SWAYAM MITTAL (https://medium.com/@swayammittal65_2667?source=email-7bc7ce57268a-1568496906514-digest.reader-------------------------bba676a2_8097_406c_b264_28c5cb1da4f0)
 in Data Driven Investor (https://medium.com/datadriveninvestor?source=email-7bc7ce57268a-1568496906514-digest.reader-------------------------bba676a2_8097_406c_b264_28c5cb1da4f0)
57 min read


Detecting Hate Speech in Tweets: Natural Language Processing in Python for… (https://medium.com/@rebecca.vickery/detecting-hate-speech-in-tweets-natural-language-processing-in-python-for-beginners-4e591952223?source=email-7bc7ce57268a-1568496906514-digest.reader------2-59------------------bba676a2_8097_406c_b264_28c5cb1da4f0-1-----&sectionName=top)

Get up and running with some code to perform text classification in Python.
Rebecca Vickery (https://medium.com/@rebecca.vickery?source=email-7bc7ce57268a-1568496906514-digest.reader-------------------------bba676a2_8097_406c_b264_28c5cb1da4f0)
 in vickdata (https://medium.com/vickdata?source=email-7bc7ce57268a-1568496906514-digest.reader-------------------------bba676a2_8097_406c_b264_28c5cb1da4f0)
7 min read


JSON - The Python Way (https://medium.com/@mc_alila/json-the-python-way-91aac95d4041?source=email-7bc7ce57268a-1568496906514-digest.reader------3-59------------------bba676a2_8097_406c_b264_28c5cb1da4f0-1-----&sectionName=top)

What is JSON ? - The Fat-Free Alternative to XML.
The Fellow (https://medium.com/@mc_alila?source=email-7bc7ce57268a-1568496906514-digest.reader-------------------------bba676a2_8097_406c_b264_28c5cb1da4f0)
 in Python Pandemonium (https://medium.com/python-pandemonium?source=email-7bc7ce57268a-1568496906514-digest.reader-------------------------bba676a2_8097_406c_b264_28c5cb1da4f0)
7 min read

Quick reads

Sentiment Analysis on US Twitter Airlines dataset: a deep learning approach (https://medium.com/@claudioakaklaus/sentiment-analysis-on-us-twitter-airlines-dataset-a-deep-learning-approach-885959366d32?source=email-7bc7ce57268a-1568496906514-digest.reader------0-72------------------bba676a2_8097_406c_b264_28c5cb1da4f0-28-----&sectionName=quickReads)

In two of my previous posts (this and this), I tried to make a sentiment analysis on the twitter airline data…
Claudio Masolo (https://medium.com/@claudioakaklaus?source=email-7bc7ce57268a-1568496906514-digest.reader-------------------------bba676a2_8097_406c_b264_28c5cb1da4f0)
2 min read


All Suffering Is Desiring or Resisting Change (https://medium.com/@ngoeke/all-suffering-is-desiring-or-resisting-change-988d1b359ee3?source=email-7bc7ce57268a-1568496906514-digest.reader------1-72------------------bba676a2_8097_406c_b264_28c5cb1da4f0-28-----&sectionName=quickReads)

Accept life is fragile, and your emotional pain will disappear
Niklas Göke (https://medium.com/@ngoeke?source=email-7bc7ce57268a-1568496906514-digest.reader-------------------------bba676a2_8097_406c_b264_28c5cb1da4f0)
4 min read

Based on your reading history

Python Pandas Data Frame Basics. (https://medium.com/@tanunprabhu95/python-pandas-data-frame-basics-b5cfbcd8c039?source=email-7bc7ce57268a-1568496906514-digest.reader------0-59------------------bba676a2_8097_406c_b264_28c5cb1da4f0-16-----&sectionName=recommended)

Let us understand the basics of Pandas DataFrame from scratch.
Tanu N Prabhu (https://medium.com/@tanunprabhu95?source=email-7bc7ce57268a-1568496906514-digest.reader-------------------------bba676a2_8097_406c_b264_28c5cb1da4f0)
 in Towards Data Science (https://medium.com/towards-data-science?source=email-7bc7ce57268a-1568496906514-digest.reader-------------------------bba676a2_8097_406c_b264_28c5cb1da4f0)
6 min read


Beginner's Recommendation Systems with Python (https://medium.com/@jds2be/beginners-recommendation-systems-with-python-ee1b08d2efb6?source=email-7bc7ce57268a-1568496906514-digest.reader------1-59------------------bba676a2_8097_406c_b264_28c5cb1da4f0-16-----&sectionName=recommended)

Building our own recommendation systems with the TMDB 5000 movies dataset
Dean Sublett (https://medium.com/@jds2be?source=email-7bc7ce57268a-1568496906514-digest.reader-------------------------bba676a2_8097_406c_b264_28c5cb1da4f0)
 in Towards Data Science (https://medium.com/towards-data-science?source=email-7bc7ce57268a-1568496906514-digest.reader-------------------------bba676a2_8097_406c_b264_28c5cb1da4f0)
6 min read


How To Develop Your First Web Crawler Using Python Scrapy (https://medium.com/@pknerd/develop-your-first-web-crawler-in-python-scrapy-6b2ee4baf954?source=email-7bc7ce57268a-1568496906514-digest.reader------2-59------------------bba676a2_8097_406c_b264_28c5cb1da4f0-16-----&sectionName=recommended)

Crawlers for searches across multiple pages
Adnan Siddiqi (https://medium.com/@pknerd?source=email-7bc7ce57268a-1568496906514-digest.reader-------------------------bba676a2_8097_406c_b264_28c5cb1da4f0)
 in Better Programming (https://medium.com/better-programming?source=email-7bc7ce57268a-1568496906514-digest.reader-------------------------bba676a2_8097_406c_b264_28c5cb1da4f0)

subject: SANKALAN 2019
body:
Hey Everyone !

First and foremost, wish you all a very* Happy new year.*

Now that you all are well acquainted to DUCS trends, it's time for a whole
new experience that comes with what we take pride in, the annual technical
fest-Sankalan. With the onset of a new year, it's time to keep the
enthusiasm going and resolve to make Sankalan '19 bigger and better.

We are all part of the DUCS Society just like you had your department
societies back in college.
Just to notify few important things before you be part of this extravaganza
we will have a meeting on tuesday i.e. *8 January 2019 at 2 pm* in *seminar
room*.

Everyone's presence is compulsory.

Regards,

SANKALAN 2019 panel
Department of Computer Science,
University of Delhi

subject:
Fwd: ShareChat is offering exclusive internship opportunities for
 final year students
body:
Are you placed in your dream company but still crave for a startup
experience? Here you go! ShareChat is offering an exclusive internship
opportunity for final year B.Tech students who want to get an exposure at a
startup before starting their professional journey.


ShareChat is India’s fastest growing social network has amassed a user-base
of 18+ millions and it’s still growing. So if you are someone who still
yearns to be a part of the startup culture and would like to give it a shot
before joining your dream company then this is a best opportunity for you!
ShareChat is hiring interns for the following roles:

   - *Backend Intern *(stipend: INR 75K/month)
   - *Android Intern *(stipend: INR 75K/month)
   - *Web Development Intern *(stipend: INR 75K/month)
   - *Machine Learning Intern *(stipend: INR 75K/month)

ShareChat already has a user-base of millions of users and now they are
ready to take on the challenges of reaching out to their next billion
users. To be a part of ShareChat, all you need to do is take part in the
March Cook-Off and fill up the application form mentioned below:

   - *Contest link:* www.codechef.com/COOK104
   <https://mail.codechef.com/l/uEUW26uUOcUWrVysfeljTw/892X5B892wL8CvcvAdIEwtUmug/jxqsOKvV0cruSM9HKw286A>
   - *Contest start date:* 24th March at 9:30 pm IST
   - *Contest duration:* 2.5 hours
   - *Application form: *https://goo.gl/gGZv89
   <https://mail.codechef.com/l/uEUW26uUOcUWrVysfeljTw/BdSoFA3AcnHCvfggZAmXwg/jxqsOKvV0cruSM9HKw286A>

*Location:* Bangalore

*Note: *Accomodation and travel for the internship will be taken care by
ShareChat. More details about the internship roles can be found here:
https://goo.gl/NYKo1K
<https://mail.codechef.com/l/uEUW26uUOcUWrVysfeljTw/lFjGaYFqDtGwwMp892rfNQhw/jxqsOKvV0cruSM9HKw286A>

We hope you’ll make the most of this wonderful opportunity! In case of any
queries, please feel free to write to us at contests@codechef.com

Regards,
*Rima Jethmalani*
Team CodeChef

Unsubscribe here
<https://mail.codechef.com/unsubscribe/GKmh9mVpP6bziav6MloejvTbevKlIZaR8kHrGGplI3c/JW892viGr7638929ohZByDLiUTaQ/jxqsOKvV0cruSM9HKw286A>

subject: AWS Educate
body:
Hello Folks
Here's AWS training and certification Course. This course demonstrates how
to efficiently use AWS security services to stay secure in the AWS Cloud.
You can enroll it for free.

Steps for applying:
- Open Link: https://aws.amazon.com/education/awseducate/
- Fill Form and you'll get a mail regarding your application
- Read mail and Upload Your Student ID Card
- If Approved, then You can access AWS Educate

Kindly go through the given link and read all instructions. Apply if
Interested.

Thank you

Regards

*Mohd Shoaib Rayeen*

*Master of Computer Application*

Department of Computer Science

( Faculty of Mathematical Sciences ) ,

University of Delhi, New Delhi - 110007
Mobile : +91-(818)-181-3999

subject: Srijan'19 Panel Selection
body:
Srijan’19

Annual Tech Magazine of Department of Computer Science


Greetings to you all,

With a new academic year, DUCS is all set to offer you new opportunities.
The Opportunity to pursue your creativity and be a part of something
bigger!  We are here with yet another facet of this department, Srijan, the
annual tech magazine of DUCS.

The Srijan Panel currently consists of 4 members:

Editors -

Jatin Rohilla - MCA 2nd year
( jatin.mca17.du@gmail.com )

Ashita Diwan - MSc. 2nd year
( ashita.mcs17.du@gmail.com )

Designers -

Vipin Kumar - MCA 2nd year
( vipin.mca17.du@gmail.com )

Shreshth Saxena - MSc. 2nd year
( shreshth.mcs17.du@gmail.com )

Every year on Sankalan, the annual technical fest of DUCS, we release a new
edition of Srijan, the annual tech magazine of DUCS. This year will
continue the legacy and take it even further.

We are looking for a responsible, creative and dedicated team to lead and
work with us on this new edition of Srijan. So, If you are one of those who
looks for constructive recreation, join Srijan.

The selection process for the Srijan 2019 Panel is explained in the
attachment. Kindly go through it, and do as needed before the deadline. The
recent edition of Srijan is also attached in the mail. Please go through it
for reference. For previous editions, feel free to check out our website
https://www.ducs.in/srijan/

For any queries, drop a message to any of the panelists. You can also reach
us at  ducs-srijan-2019@googlegroups.com, ducs.srijan@gmail.com

All the Best!



 Srijan2018.pdf
<https://drive.google.com/file/d/1gDKLaS1btcSoObRikAJXarPHMoTwDMby/view?usp=drive_web>

subject: Placement Class on 07-02-19
body:
Greetings!

A placement class has been scheduled in the month of February.
*Date: 07-02-19*
*Time: 9AM - 5PM*
Mentor for the session will be
*Gaurav Kumar. *The class will start sharp at 9. *All are expected to be on
time.*
An hour-wise agenda of the session will be communicated shortly.

*Must revise topics before attending the class*

1. Introduction about complexities and order of complexities, eg
O(logn)<O(n)<O(n^2)

2. Array(with complexities): What? Why? how to put value in Array? how to
remove value from an array?



3. LinkList(with complexities):  what ? why? create ? delete ?
deleteAtAnyPosition? insertAtHead?insertAtAnyPostion?



4. Stack and Queues(with complexities) : What? Why? Enqueue/push and
dequeue/pop ?



5. Trees(with complexities): difference binary tree and BST? preOrder,
postOrder, inOrder, levelOrder traversal.



6. Graphs (with complexities): What? Why? bfs,dfs.


7. Please revise these algorithms with complexities:

i) Bubble sort

ii) Insertion sort

iii) Heap sort

iv) Merge sort

v) Quick sort

vi) Count sort

vii) Radix sort


Algorithm? Time complexity? Stable? Space?


8. Tries(with complexities)

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zIjfhVPRZCg



9. Heap(with complexities)

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=t0Cq6tVNRBA&t=430s



10. Hashing (with complexities)

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=shs0KM3wKv8



11. Recursion.


The mentor has also asked us to practice the coding part of these
topics in *pen-paper
based style.*

*Placement Coordinators 2019-2020*

subject: Invitation for NAAC Peer Team Meeting
body:
Dear Student

Greetings !

                On behalf of the University of Delhi, I offer felicitations
to you for being a part of this University, which is one of the most
distinguished university in the country. It is heartening to note that your
University has been ranked No 1 by the Centre for World University ranking
(CWUR, 2017) and No 2 among Universities in the QS ranking 2019 at the
National level. It has also been ranked in top 1% of the Universities in
the BRICS Region.

                You would be happy to know that based on the report
submitted  by the University and feedback given by many of you, the
National Assessment and Accreditation Council (NAAC) has decided to visit
our University from 29th  to 31st of October’ 2018. Since this
accreditation is expected to further strengthen the coveted position of the
University it is our cherished duty to contribute our part in the impending
NAAC visit.

                *As part of the scheduled visit, the NAAC Peer team will
meet students on 30.10.2018 (Tuesday) at 3:30 pm in the Convention Hall,
Vice Regal Lodge.  You are advised to report at the venue by 02:45 pm on
30.10.2018 (Tuesday). You are also advised to carry your I-card for
security reasons and verification.*

                Since your understanding about the University and its
components will help in the Assessment by the NAAC Peer team, you are
requested to be present for the meeting and share your views with Peer team
members. We are glad to mention  that your response in all earlier surveys
regarding “overall academic experience” always remained “very good” , which
reflects overall quality of  academic and research programmes being offered
by the University.

                Once again, we request you to be present in the meeting
with NAAC Peer team on *30/10/2018 (Tuesday) at 03:30 pm.* This would be
very valuable contribution to ensure that the University of Delhi completes
the accreditation exercise successfully.

Wishing you the very best for your future.



With best wishes

Dean Academic Activities and Project

subject: Fwd: For CRs of all classes
body:
Please forward this mail to all groups of your class.

---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: vasudha bhatnagar <vasudhabhatnagar@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, Feb 12, 2019 at 2:20 PM
Subject: For CRs of all classes
To: Computer Science Office <office.cs.du@gmail.com>


Dear Students,

With the prolific penetration of AI in day-to-day lives, there are concerns
regarding the ethical use of AI, legal issues due to malfunction of AI
systems,  possible threats etc..  A colloquium is being organized to
discuss such issues.
Following is the link to the website.

http://www.cmsindia.org/aiforbetterworld/

https://cyber.harvard.edu/topics/ethics-and-governance-ai

https://www.media.mit.edu/courses/the-ethics-and-governance-of-artificial-intelligence/

Please register (it is free today) for the colloquium to be aware of the
frontiers of Computational Sciences today.

Following additional links will indicate the importance of the subject.

Some volunteers are also required for writing notes of the session (FCFS
basis).

Best wishes

Vasudha Bhatnagar
Deptt. of Computer Science
University of Delhi, Delhi,  India.
Homepage: people.du.ac.in/~vbhatnagar/

 on CEU MS in Finance, MS in Business Analytics
body:
Regards
Office
Department of Computer Science
University of Delhi
Delhi-110007


---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: vasudha bhatnagar <vasudhabhatnagar@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, Jan 25, 2019 at 11:14 AM
Subject: Fwd: London hedge fund, Morgan Stanley Budapest
scholarships/internships on CEU MS in Finance, MS in Business Analytics
To: compsc_du <compsc_du@googlegroups.com>


FYI.

Vasudha Bhatnagar
Deptt. of Computer Science
University of Delhi, Delhi,  India.
Homepage: people.du.ac.in/~vbhatnagar/


---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: Dean International Relations DU <deanir.du@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, Jan 24, 2019 at 11:18 AM
Subject: Fwd: London hedge fund, Morgan Stanley Budapest
scholarships/internships on CEU MS in Finance, MS in Business Analytics
To: vasudha bhatnagar <vasudhabhatnagar@gmail.com>, <head@maths.du.ac.in>, <
dustatistics@gmail.com>, <anant@econdse.org>


Kindly see if any of your students are interested to apply.  The deadline
is very near, January 31, 2019.

With regards,
Deepa Gupta

---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: Peter Szilagyi <SzilagyiP@ceu.edu>
Date: Thu, Jan 24, 2019 at 6:49 AM
Subject: London hedge fund, Morgan Stanley Budapest
scholarships/internships on CEU MS in Finance, MS in Business Analytics
To: deanir.du@gmail.com <deanir.du@gmail.com>


Dear International Office,



I am Associate Professor and Head of MS in Finance at Central European
University.



We have just been able to confirm the 2019-20 scholarship/internship
programs on CEU’s MS in Finance and MS in Business Analytics:

- Future of Big Data: Up to 3 scholarships/internships with a London
boutique hedge fund.

- Morgan Stanley: Up to 5 scholarships/internships with Morgan Stanley’s
Budapest office.

- Women in Technology: Up to 4 scholarships with one-on-one mentoring by
industry partners and faculty.



Unfortunately, the application deadline is rather tight at January 31,
hence my request to you.



Could you please share the attached poster or the links below with your
graduating students and alumni? Applicants must have a quant background
i.e. economics, statistics, science, computer science, statistics,
mathematics, engineering etc.

https://economics.ceu.edu/article/2019-01-06/ms-business-analytics-ms-finance-scholarships-apply-31-january

https://www.facebook.com/ceueconbusiness/posts/10156068720515954

https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:6487722789275992064



CEU is a U.S. graduate university with campuses in Budapest and Vienna. It
is ranked #151-200 and CEE #2 in economics by QS and ARWU ShanghaiRanking.
The MS in Business Analytics and MS in Finance are ranked #50 and #89,
respectively, by QS. The programs are based primarily in Budapest, and are
designed to allow students to enter an internship or job at any time.



Thank you very much for your help.



Kind regards,

Peter



*Peter G. Szilagyi, PhD*

*Associate Professor, Head of MS in Finance*

*CEU InnovationsLab Head of FinTech Section*

*Editor, Journal of Multinational Financial Management*

CENTRAL EUROPEAN UNIVERSITY

Nador u. 9 | 1051 Budapest, Hungary

+36 20 553 6006 | szilagyip@ceu.edu

people.ceu.edu/peter_szilagyi | linkedin.com/in/pgszilagyi

economics.ceu.edu/program/master-science-finance

subject: Presentation on student managed dept website
body:
Hi folks!

I'll be doing a presentation on the student managed DUCS website
(ducs.in, not cs.du.ac.in) that hosts our major events: Sankalan and
Srijan, since 2018. The presentation will be held on Friday, Nov 16,
2018 13:00 IST, place - seminar hall (or wherever). You're all invited
to join!

The agenda will be as follows:
- 🤷‍♂️ why that website exists
- ✨ how that website works - a demo of the website
- 🤓 how the website was built - so you can learn about its build
system and maybe reuse some of it for next year.
- 🚀 how it was deployed
- ⚛ future of website
- 🙋‍♂️ questions

Looks like you'll see my once more 😉

Regards
Sudhanshu Vishnoi
MCA 3rd year (2016-2019)

--

subject:
Announcing all-expenses paid tour of hottest Silicon Valley tech
 companies!
body:
Hi Megha,

We are excited to announce our ninth Tech Tour this summer 2019, where we will be inviting 10 finalists to an all-expenses paid behind-the-scenes tour of several of the hottest tech companies in Silicon Valley.

I invite you to apply here: www.piazza.com/techtour

In order to apply, all you have to do is update your Piazza Careers profile with the latest copy of your resume (don't worry if it's not completely up to date) and fill out a few profile questions. Applications are due March 31st, 2019 at 9am PST. Finalists will be announced on May 31st, 2019 at 9am PST.

We at Piazza have made it our life’s mission to empower young individuals in their coursework and career to excel; our tech tours are an avenue by which we see a path to students broadening their horizons by learning what’s out there. We’ve been humbled with the positive feedback we’ve received from our finalists from prior tech tours on their experience till date engaging with the companies we select to participate.

Thanks and good luck,
Pooja<
CEO & Founder, Piazza

P.S. Check out our 2017 tech tour here! https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qVuprSMlZ38&feature=youtu.be

If this email was an inconvenience, please opt out from future opportunity notifications here: https://piazza.com/careers/unsubscribe_tour?uid=jm0r3jx58f31iq, and I will be sure not to contact you again.
Error in opting out? Opt in here: https://piazza.com/careers/resubscribe_tour?uid=jm0r3jx58f31iq

subject: WORKSHOP on Machine Learning at CETPA INFOTECH PVT LTD (20th July 2019)
body:
*Dear All*

*Greetings of the day!*


*IEEE Young Professionals Delhi Section is going to organize a WORKSHOP on
Machine Learning at CETPA INFOTECH PVT LTD (20th July 2019).*

*Machine Learning is the science of getting computers to act without being
explicitly programmed. In the past decade, machine learning has given us
self-driving cars, practical speech recognition, effective web search, and
a vastly improved understanding of the human genome.*

*It is so pervasive today that you probably use it dozens of times a day
without knowing it. Many researchers also think it is the best way to make
progress towards human-level AI.*

*Learn about tomorrow’s technology today with our 2 hours workshop on
Machine Learning.*

*The workshop is organized by IEEE Young Professional targeting young
professional members, research fellows, and undergraduates. *


*Date: July 20, 2019 *

*Timing: 12-3 pm*

*Venue: CETPA INFOTECH PVT LTD D-58, SECTOR 2 NOIDA.*

*The Registration link is as follows:*

https://forms.gle/1xu81j7VBzG2j1Td7


Thanks & Regards

*Dr. Priyanka Rathee*
*Chairperson*
*IEEE Young Professionals,*
* Delhi Section*

*Assistant Professor*

*Department of Computer Science *

*(Faculty of Mathematical Sciences)*

*1st Floor, New Academic Block *

*University of Delhi *

*Delhi - 110007. India.*


*Find me on linkedin here: *www.linkedin.com/in/priyanka-rathee-31066667

body:

Delhi-110007


---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: Vasudha Bhatnagar <vbhatnagar@cs.du.ac.in>
Date: Wed, Jul 3, 2019 at 9:19 AM
Subject: Fwd: University of Delhi, Delhi | ETHIndia 2.0
To: office cs du <office.cs.du@gmail.com>


please email to all CRs

------------------------------
*From: *"Eshan Arora" <thisiseshan@gmail.com>
*To: *vc@du.ac.in, "Vasudha Bhatnagar" <vbhatnagar@cs.du.ac.in>
*Cc: *placement@du.ac.in
*Sent: *Tuesday, July 2, 2019 3:45:49 PM
*Subject: *University of Delhi, Delhi | ETHIndia 2.0

Dear Sir/Ma'am,

I’m part of the organizing team of Asia’s biggest Ethereum blockchain
hackathon: ETHIndia and we’d love to have student’s participation from your
institute. Please circulate ETHIndia details within the student community
as you seem fit. I’m sharing the blurb with you:

The wait is finally over for the second iteration of the massively
anticipated ETHIndia 2.0 <http://ethindia.co/> happening in Bangalore on
2-4 August 2019. The first edition <http://2018.ethindia.co/> of ETHIndia
saw 400+ attendees, 50+ submissions and even hacks which developed into wildly
successful <https://twitter.com/InstaDApp/status/1102602738058186752>
real-world
products. The best part is that knowledge of blockchain
<https://medium.com/ethindia/newbie-guide-to-blockchain-programming-a64f5186a57f>
 is not a pre-requisite to apply!

In addition, the following perks make it a must-attend for the
technologically inclined:

* Registrations are free of cost.

* The organizers will take care of travel reimbursements for accepted
students.

* With a host of crypto companies and startups in tow as sponsors,
including Ethereum Foundation <https://www.ethereum.org/>, ETHGlobal
<https://ethglobal.co/>, Torus <https://tor.us/>, ENS <https://ens.domains/>
, Devfolio <http://devfolio.co/> and the likes, the event will provide you
with the perfect platform to grab potential jobs/internships, apart from
learning about the latest in cutting edge tech from international speakers.

* Some cool merchandises/schwags will be provided to all the
participants(freeof cost).

15th July, 2019 11:59 pm IST is the last date for registration. It can be
done through the ETHIndia portal available on https://ethindia.co/

Thanks & Regards

Eshan
Team ETHIndia

------------------------------

Explore ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses )

 

DataCamp + Python: A Perfect Match ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/tech:python )

----------------------
Fun Facts About Python
----------------------

•

Python was created in 1989 by Guido van Rossum and was named after Monty Python's Flying Circus.

•

Python was the third most popular programming language of 2016.

•

Because of van Rossum's active role in the Python community, he has been dubbed "benevolent dictator for life" (BDFL).

•

If you are ever in need of some Pythonic inspiration, try running the command import this in any DataCamp Python course ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/tech:python )!

 

DataCamp + R: A Perfect Match ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/tech:r )

-----------------
Fun Facts About R
-----------------

•

R was created in New Zealand and is derived from another language called S.

•

R was the fifth most popular programming language of 2016.

•

The name "R" was chosen because of the creators' first names (Ross Ihaka and Robert Gentleman, "R & R").

•

The idea for R came about in 1992 and the first stable version was available in 2000. R has come a long way since then!

subject: Important: The Google Advertiser Community has moved to a new platform
body:
Important: The Google Advertiser Community has moved to a new platform




You're receiving this email because you've registered in our Google  
Advertiser Community in the past. Please read the frequently asked  
questions below to learn about the migration and how to save your community  
content before the full migration happens.

What's happening?

In April 2019, the Google Advertiser Community moved to its own community  
platform, which is integrated into our product help centers ( Google Ads,  
Google My Business, Google Analytics, etc.). The only exception to this is  
Google Partners, which is a part of the Google Ads forums for English,  
Turkish, Portuguese (pt-BR) and Japanese languages.

How do I access the new forums?

You can view the new forums and post questions by visiting your product's  
help center and then clicking on the “Community” tab, or by visiting the  
URLs below:


Google Ads Forum
Google My Business Forum
Google Analytics Forum

To change the language of the community, simply scroll the webpage to the  
bottom, click the down arrow in the drop-down menu, and select the language  
you want.

What markets and languages will be affected by the migration?

While some markets won't be initially supported, we're working on launching  
community forums for previously supported Google Ads languages. If you find  
that the product forum isn't available for your locale at launch, please  
let us know on the English forum for your product.

What will happen to our community content?

Content that was previously posted on Lithium will remain available in  
read-only mode. Most content was migrated and is already available on the  
new platform. By July 2019, the Google Advertiser Community will no longer  
be available on the Lithium platform.

How do I export my Lithium community content?

Important


To download your Lithium content, please read the instructions below. These  
procedures will be in effect only until we shut down Lithium in July 2019.


In the Google Advertiser Community, click your email address in the left  
navigation bar and select My Settings on the drop-down menu.
On the "Personal tab," select Personal Information.
Scroll the page down and find links to download your personal data and  
community content.

How to close your Lithium account and delete your activity from all forums

Important


Closing your Lithium account will delete only your forum activity on  
Lithium and cannot be reversed.


In the Google Advertiser Community, click your email address in the left  
navigation bar and select My Settings on the drop-down menu.
On the "Personal tab," select Close Account.
Click Close Account.

We look forward to engaging with you in our new platform!




Sincerely,




The Google Advertiser Community




You've received this mandatory email service announcement to update you  
about important changes to your Google Advertiser Community account.


Google

Google LLC
1600 Amphitheatre Parkway,
Mountain View, CA 94043

subject: Intra-Sankalan 2019
body:
Hello everyone,

We take great pleasure in informing you that the Intra Sankalan will take
place on *8th-9th February 2019. ( Friday and Saturday )*

The following is the list of events -


1. Algoholics -  This event is aimed at testing the proficiency of
participants in algorithms. Teams qualifying for the mains will be given
algorithmic problems to be solved overnight.

2. BrainSpark -  Participating teams must survive a set of aptitude,
reasoning and logical questions to enter the final round to face more
brain-racking puzzles.

3. Chakravyuh :-  This is an online treasure hunt event. At each level, a
question will be posed and hints may be given. A participant must answer
correctly to advance to the next level.

4. Code-a-thon -  In this coding event, teams will be given programming
problems to solve and code. Code can be done on any language.

5. Mind Matters - This is a technical quizzing event. The participants will
be quizzed on their knowledge and awareness in different IT fields.

6. Select * From Brain  - In this event, DBMS and RDBMS concepts will be
the primary key to advance through the prelims. In the final round, teams
will be required to query a given database.

7. Spin-a-web -This is a website development event to test your web
development skills. You will be given a take-home problem to code
overnight. Products are judged on the basis of feature-completeness and UI.

8. Cypher-o-More - This is a cryptographic event where you will have to
bring out the Alan Turing in you and solve the encryption-decryption
problems.

9. LAN- DEN -  Gaming event comprising of various adventurous games. CS,
NFS are the two games for intra.

10. Code Auction with Blind Coding - You will buy problems from given
credits and your partner will solve them. You can either pick monitor ON or
monitor OFF for different points.

Here is the team registration form -

http://bit.ly/intra-sankalan-2019


Here is the facebook event link -

https://www.facebook.com/events/773664476343921/


Regards,

Sankalan 2019 Team

DUCS



-- 
Regards
Sankalan Panel 2019
DUCS

--

subject: Intra-Sankalan 2019
body:
Hello everyone,

We take great pleasure in informing you that the Intra Sankalan will take
place on *8th-9th February 2019. ( Friday and Saturday )*

Intra Sankalan is a two-day event where you will participate in a team of
two. The team remains the same for all the events. So you would probably
want to make your teams accordingly. You can pair up with any first-year
student from DUCS ( MCA as well as MSc ).

Registrations for the same will begin shortly.

Intra Sankalan mainly focuses on technical events. The list of events for
this year’s intra sankalan are as follows -

1. Algoholics -  This event is aimed at testing the proficiency of
participants in algorithms. Teams qualifying for the mains will be given
algorithmic problems to be solved overnight.

2. BrainSpark -  Participating teams must survive a set of aptitude,
reasoning and logical questions to enter the final round to face more
brain-racking puzzles.

3. Chakravyuh :-  This is an online treasure hunt event. At each level, a
question will be posed and hints may be given. A participant must answer
correctly to advance to the next level.

4. Code-a-thon -  In this coding event, teams will be given programming
problems to solve and code. Code can be done on any language.

5. Mind Matters - This is a technical quizzing event. The participants will
be quizzed on their knowledge and awareness in different IT fields.

6. Select * From Brain  - In this event, DBMS and RDBMS concepts will be
the primary key to advance through the prelims. In the final round, teams
will be required to query a given database.

7. Spin-a-web -This is a website development event to test your web
development skills. You will be given a take-home problem to code
overnight. Products are judged on the basis of feature-completeness and UI.

8. Cypher-o-More - This is a cryptographic event where you will have to
bring out the Alan Turing in you and solve the encryption-decryption
problems.

9. LAN- DEN -  Gaming event comprising of various adventurous games. CS,
NFS are the two games for intra.

10. Code Auction with Blind Coding - You will buy problems from given
credits and your partner will solve them. You can either pick monitor ON or
monitor OFF for different points.

Intra Chakravyuh usually takes place a week before Intra Sankalan. The
timing for Intra Chakravyuh will be -

*From Saturday 2nd Feb 9pm to Sunday 3rd Feb 9pm.*


The Facebook event link is - https://www.facebook.com/ducs.chakravyuh

The URL for the actual chakravyuh website will be provided 1 hour before
the event.

The aim of Intra Sankalan is to get you familiar with events. So you all
are advised to participate in as many events as possible. The team winning
the maximum number of events will get a special prize.

Buckle up, It’s time to compete, and all the very best.

Regards,

Sankalan 2019 Team

DUCS

The aim of Intra Sankalan is to get you familiar with events. So you all
are advised to participate in as many events as possible. The team winning
the maximum number of events will get a special prize.

Buckle up, It’s time to compete, and all the very best.

Regards,

Sankalan 2019 Team

DUCS
