subject: Sankalan 2019 - Junior Coordinators preference form
body:
Hello everyone, warmest greetings to you all.
It's sankalan time of the year and to make it as bright as ever we'll need
your support. Tentative Sankalan Dates are - 2nd and 3rd March, 2019.
So, this is a good time to start preparations to stay ahead of the time.

For now, tasks have been divided into departments.
Here is a preference form for major departments of Sankalan.
https://goo.gl/forms/KLg37Q5ocOK8UOXy1

Everyone is required to submit the form by 11th January 2018 - 10pm.
Thereafter you'll be assigned to one or more teams and we'll officially
begin sankalan preparations.

And i'm sure you all know by now, but just to be explicit, Fests are not
just about the work. It's about the fun you have these few weeks, about the
classes you miss, about the interactions you have with seniors. It's about
all those laughs and parties. It's the time you realise that this is
probably the last of your fests and your life as a student will soon be
over. It's about an opportunity to meet with alumni, and hear their
experiences.
So, need not worry. Your job is to indulge with sankalan activities and fun
with come your way in latent ways. Next year, you'll be looking at this
time full of memories. Isn't that what we're doing here? Making memories.

Stay bright and feel free to reach out in case of any doubts.

Regards
Sankalan Team
DUCS

subject: Fwd: Workshop on "Awareness on E-Waste Management" on 12th April 2019
body:
Dear Students,

The Department of Computer Science in collaboration with *Karo Sambhav *(
India's leading Producer Responsibility Organization) is organizing a
workshop titled *"AWARENESS ON E-WASTE MANAGEMENT" *on 12th April 2019
(12:00 pm to 1:30 pm).

This awareness workshop will help the electronic consumers understand the
current scenario of E-waste in our country and our responsibilities in
curbing it. The details of the program are mentioned in the brochure
attached below.

Interested students need to register on the link given below by 11th April
2019 (2:00 pm). Seats are limited, so seats will be reserved on first come
first serve basis.
https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfItas5Ej7HAYFuklrhwL2a6IlY--rMNNX7yIqLRxfnvXYClQ/viewform?usp=sf_link

*Sent: *Monday, September 16, 2019 2:23:44 PM
*Subject: *Request to put up attached notice in your Department about
special colloquium in Physics Dept


Title :
*Evolution of Human *
*    Cognition*

Speaker :      *Prof.  L.S. Shashidhara*
         President, Int. Union of Biological Sciences

Affiliation:    IISER, Pune     and      Ashoka University

Date:              Sept 17, 2019 (Tuesday)

Time:             3:30 P.M.

Venue:           D.S. Kothari Lecture Hall, Department of Physics and
Astrophysics

Abstract

This talk would demonstrate similarities between the higher order
cognitive functions of humans and other animals as distant as
insects. At the same time, it will also touch upon what specific
biological traits have evolved in humans leading to the cultural
evolution that we experience today.
*The talk does not assume any *
*prior** knowledge of modern biology.*

subject: Lack of choice in elective subjects.
body:
Dear Madam

I am Samyak Ahuja from Computer Science Department of University of Delhi
presently in my 2nd year of M.Sc.

On 15th July a mail from Dr. Reena Kasana was forwarded to the class mail
group presenting a form that required the students to fill their choices
for the elective subjects that they have to take in the coming 3rd
semester. To many it came as a surprise that only 5 out of the 16 subjects
- given in the syllabus - were given as choices out of which they had to
select 3.

As a response to that I expressed my dissatisfaction to Dr. Kasana and
asked to confirm if this was definite. She then proceeded to forward me the
reply she got from the HOD of Computer Science, Prof. Bhatnagar, which said
and I quote, "due to faculty crunch, it is not possible to offer more
electives.".

Now recently on the class group, teachers for each of the 5 subjects were
announced and to everybody's amazement none of the permanent faculty
members were mentioned in that list. You can imagine the skepticism I felt
towards the response. To be honest I kind of feel humiliated by the lack of
a more definite resolution to this.

I respectfully ask you to look into the matter as to be able to study the
subject of their choosing is of great importance to a lot of students.

Thanking you

--

subject: Fwd: WORKSHOP on IT SECURITY (4th October & 18th October 2019)
body:
Dear students
The department of computer science is going to organize a workshop on IT
security on 4th and 18th October 2019. The detail about the workshop is
included in the google form. Please find the registration link as follows:


[image: Google Forms]
> Having trouble with viewing or submitting this form?
> Fill in using Google Forms
> <https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScrEwcVOcShdZJDqPkX_KavtONu8j2B8irBkNxCnAXaXoSdOQ/viewform?vc=0&c=0&w=1&usp=mail_form_link>
>
> I've invited you to fill in a form:
> WORKSHOP on IT SECURITY (4th October & 18th October 2019)
> <https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScrEwcVOcShdZJDqPkX_KavtONu8j2B8irBkNxCnAXaXoSdOQ/viewform?vc=0&c=0&w=1&usp=mail_form_link>
> The Department of Computer Science, University of Delhi is going to
> organize a workshop on IT security on 4th and 18th October 2019. The expert
> for the workshop is
>
> Mr. Anoop Kumar
> Manager, Information Systems
> Bharat Electronics Limited
> (A Govt. of India Enterprise)
> Ministry of Defense
>
> Contents for the workshop
>
> 1. The Basic
> a) Information Vs Data
> (Information: CIA, Application security, Cloud security, Infrastructure
> security, Application security, Incidents and Vulnerability management.
> Data: Encryptions, Masking, Erasure, Resilience)
>
> b) What is information technology
> (Network Security, Internet Security , End Point Security , Application
> Security)
> c) How important the Information is?
> d) ** Data/Information Communication technologies
> (Basic Networking and Devices, Servers like AD, DNS, DHCP, AV, CMS, NMS,
> Radius, NTP, WSUS etc.)
> e) IT infrastructure in any organization
> f) IT infrastructure Security(SEIM, UEBA, Secure Web
> Gateway-NGTP,IPS,IDS,IAM, NIPS,HIPS, WIPS, Patch Management)
> g) ** Network Monitoring & trouble shooting(Ping, pathping, NSlookup,
> Tracert, netstat, telnet, nslookup, arp, getmac, ipconfig, netdiag, route,
> flushdns)
> h) ** Cyber-attack Maps
> i) ** Hacking Examples
> j) ** How identify the Viruses
> k) ** Google database examples
> l) Data In Rest Vs Data in transit
> (DLP ,AV)
> m) Significance of information Security in your life
> n) Negligence in Information security can cost high loss
> o) Internet – Cyber World
> ( where your information resides,LAN ,MAN ,WAN ,PAN ,Surface ,Deep Dark
> Web)
> p) Who is a hacker?
> q) Vulnerabilities, Risk, Threats and Exploits
> r) Let us Know what is in the hacker mind
> s) Shadow IT
> t) Form Jacking
> u) Digital Foot Print
> v) Harding and Monitoring
> w) Multi factor authentication
>
> 2. Techniques that breach your information security
> a) ** Malwares(Types Trojan, Virus, Warms etc. and examples)
> I. Types of malware.
> II. How malware affects your data.
> III. Anti Malware Strategies.
> b) Attacks Vectors, Surface and paths (Active and Passive Attacks)
> I. Active Attacks
> II. Passive Attacks
> III. Common types of cyber attack types
> c) Types of hackers
> d) ** Types of hacking
> e) **Known and Unknown Vulnerabilities
> f) **Your Negligence – Hacker Success( Fake Mails-Outlook example)
> I. Attacker motivation
> g) The Computer Security Environment Today
> I. Information security culture
> II. Impact of security breaches
> h) Security Frameworks
> I. Functions and categories of cyber security activities
> II. Identify
> III. Protect
> IV. Detect
> V. Respond
> VI. Recover
> i) ** Advanced Web Attacks and Exploitation
> j) Managing security risks: risk analysis and management
> k) ** Web Security – OWASP top ten
> l) Security Standards (ISMS, PCI, NIST etc.)
> m) Wireless/Wi-Fi Security
>
> 3. How to protect
> n) Best Practices and Recommendations
> o) security controls (Physical and Logical)
> p) Incident response
> q) Organizational security
> r) Encryption and Cryptography
>
> ** Topics will cover with practical and some live examples.
>
> The content given above will be covered in two parts.
> The dates of the workshop are:
> IT security workshop part1: 4th October 2019.
> IT security workshop part2: 18th October 2019.
> Time of workshop: 2-5 pm
>
> Venue of workshop: Seminar Hall, Department of computer science, North
> Campus, University of Delhi.
>
> Note: The students are advised to register only if they are keenly
> interested to learn. After registration, the presence in the workshop will
> be mandatory. Failing those will be banned for future workshops.
> There are limited seats for workshop. Only 15 students from each class
> will be considered on first come first serve basis.
>
>
>    Registration form
>    The Students/research scholars need to fill the following form to
>    reserve their seat for workshop.
>    Name
>    College/Department
>    Email id
>    Phone number
>    Never submit passwords through Google Forms.
>
> Powered by
> [image: Google Forms]
>
> <https://www.google.com/forms/about/?utm_source=product&utm_medium=forms_logo&utm_campaign=forms>
> This content is neither created nor endorsed by Google.
> Report Abuse
> <https://docs.google.com/forms/u/0/d/e/1FAIpQLScrEwcVOcShdZJDqPkX_KavtONu8j2B8irBkNxCnAXaXoSdOQ/reportabuse?source=https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScrEwcVOcShdZJDqPkX_KavtONu8j2B8irBkNxCnAXaXoSdOQ/viewform?sid%3D357c02be4945ae95%26vc%3D0%26c%3D0%26w%3D1%26token%3DjoxzSG0BAAA.kxvB69vwwyQtsluofjZiuA.ofrKeF8j3irqRuT-Y8CNgg>
> - Terms of Service <http://www.google.com/accounts/TOS> - Additional Terms
> <http://www.google.com/google-d-s/terms.html>
> Create your own Google Form
> <https://docs.google.com/forms?usp=mail_form_link>
>

body:
Are you still interested in this job? ---------------------------------------------------------------- Your saved jobs ---------------------------------------------------------------- Amazon Associate, Quality Services Chennai, IN Expires on September 7 Apply to this job https://www.linkedin.com/comm/jobs/view/1420169632?refId=64fc19be-e6c4-4fc2-9b1f-79489be4c29a&trk=eml-sjr-top-apply-cta&midToken=AQElDMfP3_zyVA&trkEmail=eml-email_jobs_saved_job_reminder_01-null-0-null-null-chi7mu%7Ejz4bb8gu%7Eql-null-jobs%7Eview&lipi=urn%3Ali%3Apage%3Aemail_email_jobs_saved_job_reminder_01%3BD0xDW3FqTh%2BgdvEW9Nu1sw%3D%3D ---------------------------------------------------------------- Connections at Amazon ---------------------------------------------------------------- Shoaib Rayeen Alexa Campus Influencer ---------------------------------------------------------------- Job description ---------------------------------------------------------------- Description

A Device Associate’s primary responsibility is to execute test case instructions and report discrepancies. A DA is also responsible for successful and on time delivery of results.
Roles & Responsibilities
  • Execute test cases prepared for testing Software builds on the Kindle platform and Kindle software products.
  • Perform test case execution and report bugs accurately
  • Understand testing procedures and guidelines for new builds / releases.
  • Perform regression and repetitive testing exercises to qualify builds without compromising on quality
  • Use software tools for data capture on a daily basis
  • Be comfortable with capturing results, communicating and escalating failures and providing individual status reports
  • Raising all failures/doubts related to the execution of test cases in the clarification portal and closing the same as per the SLA’s

Basic Qualifications

A graduate in any field of study. Quantitative fields such as science and engineering preferred but not mandatory
  • Good familiarity with the Windows desktop environment and use of Word, Excel, IE, Firefox etc. are required
  • Flexibility and Interest to do repetitive tasks is required
  • High level of energy and proactive nature. A sense of ownership and drive and a willingness to accept the challenge of daily deadlines is essential

Preferred Qualifications

A graduate in any field of study. Quantitative fields such as science and engineering preferred but not mandatory
  • Good familiarity with the Windows desktop environment and use of Word, Excel, IE, Firefox etc. are required
  • Flexibility and Interest to do repetitive tasks is required
  • High level of energy and proactive nature. A sense of ownership and drive and a willingness to accept the challenge of daily deadlines is essential

Company - ADCI - Tamil Nadu

subject: Clarification over a comment I made on Alexa Skills during GSoC presentation
body:
Hi folks!

During my GSoC presentation yesterday, I made snarky comment over
Alexa Skills on them being non-substantial (or valuable). This email
serves as a clarification on what I meant to say and why.

I was not aware that the ZooHackathon team had made an Alexa skill
during the competition. I came to know of that today. So, this also
serves as an apology if you felt bad when I made that comment. The
intention was clearly not to do any kind of personal attack.

The comment I made was based on a trend I see in the department
regarding creation of Alexa/Google Assistant Skills. The trend goes
like: Create a random fact skill (or similar), publish it, post it for
promotion and maybe add it to your resume.
What I dislike here is, there is no creativity in this. There is no
learning curve for you. Making them is not even a challenge (it's
nothing "technical" per se, and I'm calling it "making" instead of
"developing"). In a way, you're just creating free apps for some giant
corporate and wasting your time, energy and potential when you can
solve an actual problem, or learn something.
Doing it for perks is kind of fine. A T-shirt is cool. But is it worth
it? There are better ways to earn swag. Do you think this is the best
utilization of your resources (mainly time) you're doing?
The platforms like Alexa/Google Assistant have potential, but it is
directed more towards the entertainment industry than towards
something more useful in general. If you're developing apps for them,
I would like if you build something that adds value to the community.
If you have a look, the innovation is coming from the side that are
parsing your textual commands (what your code is) and converting them
into actions that the voice assistant has to make. There is some cool
technology in processing user's voice commands. Doing something like
that is more of development than creating JSON documents.
But that is just my personal opinion, some others may have similar.

Keep learning and keep developing cool useful stuff!

Regards
Sudhanshu Vishnoi
MCA 3rd year (2016-19)

subject: Fresher's 2019
body:
Hello,
    We are planning to organize Fresher's 2019 on 19th October 2019
(Saturday). We request you to come forward and help us to make this event a
success as well as worth remembering for our juniors.

subject: Anchoring Auditions and Panel Elections 2019-20
body:
Hello Juniors,

As conveyed earlier, *Anchoring auditions* for the before mentioned events
will be held tomorrow at 12 PM  followed by *Panel Elections* for the
session 2019-20 at 1 PM in seminar room.

Before elections, NK sir will address all the first year students. So, All
of you are expected to come for voting and make your opinions matter.
Remember, your single vote can turn the tables. Make sure it turn at the
right side.

We would again like to remind you that that only those students who have
contributed to the Sankalan fund will be allowed to take part in the election
process.

Note to CRs :- In case your classes clash with scheduled election timing,
you are encouraged to sort this matter out at your level. Request the
teachers for re-scheduling or cancellation of classes, whichever is
suitable.


-- 
Regards
Sankalan Panel 2019
DUCS

subject: Algo Hw list
body:
1. Correctness of insertion sort
2. T(n) = 2T(n/2) + 1,  prove that T(n)<=an+b for all n >= n0, where a,b,n0
are constants
 3. Prove that lim n->infinity f(n)/g(n) = 0 => f(n) = o(g(n)). ( by first
definition)
 4. Prove that lim n->infinity f(n)/g(n) = c => f(n) = theta(g(n)). ( by
first definition)
5.Assume that log n = o(n) and prove that (log n)^M= o(n^€), however large
M and small €>0 be.
6. Prove that LogaN = theta(LogbN), in log base doesn't matter.
 7.Show that 2^n=o(3^n) ( by limits)
 8. T(n)=T(floor(n/2)+17) + n= O(n).
9. T(n)=T(floor(n/2+17)) + n= O(n).
10. T(n)=T(floor(n/2)) + T(ceil(n/2))+ n= O(nlogn).

subject: Placement Fund
body:
Hello Everyone!

We hope that you all are onboard for the placement preparation journey
after refreshing holidays. To make this journey of ours feasible and
convenient we will be needing funds. So each one of you is required to
deposit the amount of Rs. 1000/- for the *Placement Fund* before Jan 11,
2019.

You can give the amount in cash to any of the PCs or you can transfer
online using Google Pay to Avinash Prasad(*9555138871*).

Also, those students who default on this payment will not be made part of
placement related activities nor will they be added to a new Google Group
where all future communication, regarding placements, will take place.

Thank You!

PC Team (2019-20)

algorithms.

subject: Learn the fundamentals of AI!
body:
Hi there,

We have launched eight new courses covering Python, R, and SQL. In our Joining Data with dplyr in R course, learn the skills you'll need to join multiple tables to analyze them in combination.

We're also happy to announce that we launched two new projects in Python and SQL. In one project, you can analyze international debt data collected by The World Bank. Find out how much debt each country owes, which country owns the most debt, and more.

Finally, check out five courses that are top-rated by other DataCamp learners.

Courses

•

Transactions and Error Handling in SQL Server ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/transactions-and-error-handling-in-sql-server?utm_medium=email&utm_source=customerio&utm_campaign=course_18564 )

•

Building and Optimizing Triggers in SQL Server ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/building-and-optimizing-triggers-in-sql-server?utm_medium=email&utm_source=customerio&utm_campaign=course_16721 )

•

Applying SQL to Real-World Problems ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/applying-sql-to-real-world-problems?utm_medium=email&utm_source=customerio&utm_campaign=course_14822 )

•

Unit Testing for Data Science in Python ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/unit-testing-for-data-science-in-python?utm_medium=email&utm_source=customerio&utm_campaign=course_15974 )

•

Experimental Design in Python ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/experimental-design-in-python?utm_medium=email&utm_source=customerio&utm_campaign=course_16561 )

•

Fundamentals of AI ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/fundamentals-of-ai?utm_medium=email&utm_source=customerio&utm_campaign=course_14813 ) (in Python)

•

Introduction to AWS Boto in Python ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/introduction-to-aws-boto-in-python?utm_medium=email&utm_source=customerio&utm_campaign=course_17599 )

•

Joining Data with dplyr in R ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/joining-data-with-dplyr-in-r?utm_medium=email&utm_source=customerio&utm_campaign=course_21394 )

Projects

•

Analyze International Debt Statistics ( https://www.datacamp.com/projects/754?utm_medium=email&utm_source=customerio&utm_campaign=project_754 ) (in SQL)

•

Analyze Your Runkeeper Fitness Data ( https://www.datacamp.com/projects/727?utm_medium=email&utm_source=customerio&utm_campaign=project_727 ) (in Python)

5 Courses Recommended by DataCamp Users

•

Analyzing Business Data in SQL ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/analyzing-business-data-in-sql?utm_medium=email&utm_source=customerio&utm_campaign=course_15268 )

•

Deep Learning with Keras in Python ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/deep-learning-with-keras-in-python?utm_medium=email&utm_source=customerio&utm_campaign=course_16470 )

•

Introduction to Portfolio Analysis in Python ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/introduction-to-portfolio-analysis-in-python?utm_medium=email&utm_source=customerio&utm_campaign=course_18408 )

•

Introduction to Seaborn ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/introduction-to-seaborn?utm_medium=email&utm_source=customerio&utm_campaign=course_15192 ) (in Python)

•

Sentiment Analysis in Python ( https://www.datacamp.com/courses/sentiment-analysis-in-python?utm_medium=email&utm_source=customerio&utm_campaign=course_16852 )

Happy learning,

The DataCamp Team

DataCamp Inc. | 285 Fulton Street | Suite 61A | New York, NY 10007 | Unsubscribe ( https://www.datacamp.com/mail_preferences/4ac54d28-5852-4a8b-bc1e-efb3ffe01e5e )

subject: Intra Sankalan : Schedule Day 2
body:
Here is the updated schedule for Intra Sankalan Day 2.

The schedule has been updated to avoid maximum clashes.
In case you're part of two events happening at the same time, you'll have
to choose one out of the two. Thereafter, the vacated seat will be filled
by the waitlisted teams. You are advised to decide on the events you'll
attend.

Teams in waitlist are advised to be present as well, in case the clashes
result in a vacant position, you're up next.

Everyone else is welcome to be part of the audience.

-- 
Regards
Sankalan Panel 2019

subject: Assignment
body:
Assignments list
1. Calculate avg sorting time(take 20 instances) for insertion, quick and
merge sort and draw comparison graph. Also perform curve fitting.
2. Analysis of  T(n) = T(an) + T(bn) +n
For three cases , a+b = 1
                                a+b<1
                                a+b >1
3. Prove if p(n) = a0 + a1*n +.......adn^d
 ad>0, then
4.

subject: Srijan'19 : Submissions Invited
body:
Hello everyone,

Time to show you are as good with words as you are with code.
Department's annual tech magazine - Srijan is being planned for the session
2019 - 2020.

We are seeking submissions for the same.
You are cordially invited to send in articles, sketches, and poems to
ducs-srijan-2019@googlegroups.com
Suggested article length is 500 - 800 words.

An excel sheet has been attached with this email which contains some
suggestions for topics. You can either write on any of the topics mentioned
in the sheet or intrigue us with a new topic. In both cases, kindly update
your name in front of the topic, so we don't face any topic clashes.

The deadline for submissions is 20th February 2019. We'd really appreciate
if you send us your submissions within the deadline. We'd be happy to
publish some great content sent by you.

Please find the excel sheet for topics attached.

Regards,
Team Srijan 2019

 Srijan 2019
<https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1GBspxCciULPb-Kp0rB7cMkH1uGpngf5lvQSz-RANccQ/edit?usp=drive_web>

-- 
You received this message because you are subscribed to the Google Groups "DU MCS18" group.
To unsubscribe from this group and stop receiving emails from it, send an email to mcs18du+unsubscribe@googlegroups.com.
To post to this group, send email to mcs18du@googlegroups.com.
To view this discussion on the web visit https://groups.google.com/d/msgid/mcs18du/CAGkT%3D-ZRwe4qqrdjjGgvgUxSYSRF85_x82%2BgQci%2Br%2B-LPsdbww%40mail.gmail.com.
For more options, visit https://groups.google.com/d/optout.

---------- Forwarded message ----------
From: "AnitaB.org India" <indiaqueries@anitab.org>
Date: 24 May 2019 2:47 pm
Subject: Register for the GHCI 19 AI Codeathon only for women
To: vb.ducs@gmail.com
Cc:

It's about time that you show the world your Tech Genius!

We bring you the perfect opportunity - a carefully designed codeathon for all the women engineering students from tier 2 and tier 3 cities in India. Women students from computing and IT backgrounds can also participate.

AnitaB.org India presents the smartest codeathon of 2019 - GHCI 19 Artificial Intelligence (AI) Codeathon for Women Students sponsored by American Express and powered by Skillenza. This is a great opportunity to learn and get real-life experience of AI. Participants will also get mentored from experts in this exciting technology.

Register here

We encourage you to invite your friends and have a fun time coding, reiterating, empowering and last but not the least enjoying yourselves.

The deadline for phase 1 of the codeathon (Team Formation and Ideation) is 10 June, 2019.

Further details are available here: https://skillenza.com/challenge/ghci-19-ai-codeathon

GHCI 19 also offers students the exciting opportunity to make a Poster Submission and you could be a presenter at the conference. Click here to make a poster submission.

Best Wishes
AnitaB.org India Team

PS: This is an exclusive codeathon for women students from engineering, computing and IT backgrounds from tier 2 and tier 3 cities in India.

www.AnitaB.org | GHCIndia.AnitaB.org | Community.AnitaB.org/events

subject: Policy Discussion and Placement Class Update
body:
Greetings!

As per the discussion and voting conducted on 10/04/2019, following points
have been finalised under the placement policy for this placement batch
(2019-2020):

*i) CTC to be considered*
 CTC will be taken as the final package offered to the candidate.

*ii)** Threshold of 8 lakh*
If any student is offered a CTC greater than or equal to 8 lakh, their
placement procedure will seize then and there i.e. they will not be allowed
to sit for any more companies.

*iii)** Multiplying factor of 1.75*
 If any student is offered a CTC less than 8 lakh, the package will be
multiplied by a factor of 1.75, and he/she will be eligible only in the
companies offering a package greater than or equal to this calculated
amount.* No Padding allowed.*

*iv) At most two offers*
 No student is allowed to take more than two placement offers under any
circumstances.

*Placement Class Update*

There will be no placement class on* 13-04-2019.*
*Aditya Pancholi Sir* will be taking a placement class on* 20-04-2019.*

*Placement Coordinators 2019-2020*

--

subject: Installation and Google Colab links for Deep Learning workshop.
body:
Dear All,
Pls refer to the attached document for installing software for Deep
Learning workshop.
The hands on session may be conducted online as well...in that case
installation will not be required.
However, you are advised to come prepared with the required softwares
installed on your systems in case the need arises.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
FOR ONLINE HANDS ON SESSION-
Google Colab provides pre-installed online Python libraries with both CPU
and GPU support up to 12 hrs of free usage.
Google Colab can be accessed using Google drive. It provides a the
following specs:

GPU: 1xTesla K80 , compute 3.7, having 2496 CUDA cores , 12GB GDDR5 VRAM

CPU: 1xsingle core hyper threaded Xeon Processors @2.3Ghz i.e(1 core, 2
threads)

RAM: ~12.6 GB Available

Disk: ~33 GB Available

Feb/2019 Update: GPU instance upgraded to 319 GB free space
https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/welcome.ipynb#recent=true

Here are some links to explain how to use Google Colab with Google drive :

https://medium.com/deep-learning-turkey/google-colab-free-gpu-tutorial-e113627b9f5d

https://towardsdatascience.com/getting-started-with-google-colab-f2fff97f594c

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- 
Sapna Varshney
Assistant Professor (Adhoc)
Department of Computer Science
University of Delhi, Delhi

Megha, apply now to 'Analyst-Travelers Cheque and Prepaid Servicing
 at American Express'
body:
Are you still interested in this job? ---------------------------------------------------------------- Your saved jobs ---------------------------------------------------------------- American Express Analyst-Travelers Cheque and Prepaid Servicing Gurgaon, IN Expires on September 28 Apply to this job https://www.linkedin.com/comm/jobs/view/1418632014?refId=33db244b-dc8f-496d-93c5-f25645eaab86&trk=eml-sjr-top-apply-cta&midToken=AQElDMfP3_zyVA&trkEmail=eml-email_jobs_saved_job_reminder_01-null-0-null-null-chi7mu%7Ejzyg69d7%7Emy-null-jobs%7Eview&lipi=urn%3Ali%3Apage%3Aemail_email_jobs_saved_job_reminder_01%3BiN545cWwRc6laQJ%2BN3y%2Faw%3D%3D ---------------------------------------------------------------- Job description ---------------------------------------------------------------- Why American Express?

There’s a difference between having a job and making a difference.

American Express has been making a difference in people’s lives for over 160 years, backing them in moments big and small, granting access, tools, and resources to take on their biggest challenges and reap the greatest rewards.

We’ve also made a difference in the lives of our people, providing a culture of learning and collaboration, and helping them with what they need to succeed and thrive. We have their backs as they grow their skills, conquer new challenges, or even take time to spend with their family or community. And when they’re ready to take on a new career path, we’re right there with them, giving them the guidance and momentum into the best future they envision.

Because we believe that the best way to back our customers is to back our people.

The powerful backing of American Express.

Don’t make a difference without it.

Don’t live life without it.

Function Description
  • Professionally receive and respond to sellers’ queries on re-supplies, settlements, encashment assistance, acceptance and any other Travelers Cheque and Global Travelers Cheque related matters. Refer sellers promptly and courteously.
  • Follow up with key linkages and the sellers to collect the funds due to American Express and assist Recon team in resolving the exceptions.
Purpose Of The Role
  • Manage inbound customer service calls from American Express Selling Partners and customers for Inventory Control, settlement questions/issues and various other services.
  • Interpret risk or fraud data to determine exposure and act to balance service and risk, ensuring appropriate and cost-effective decisions and alerting corresponding systems to prevent additional exposure.
  • Manage inventory levels at sellers’ end and take appropriate actions to reduce exposure to the company.
  • Hold monthly, quarterly calls with Key selling partners in the region to build relationship, continually check for acceptable quality service levels and address concerns.
  • Support the Client Management team in various regional projects.
Responsibilities
  • Support and service our customers on all their queries.
  • always Ensure delivery of quality customer service at all times by achieving appropriate service levels (as per laid out guidelines) and exceed quality standards on a consistent basis.
  • Support Six Sigma initiatives in the region. This role may be subject to additional background verification checks This role may be subject to additional background verification checks.
Qualifications

Critical Factors to Success:
  • Good oral and written communications skills necessary to interact with global linkages (both internal & external).
  • Good analytical and problem-solving skills with close attention to detail.
  • Good diversity skills - able to work in a multi-cultural, multi-lingual group.
  • Must be able to meet deadlines to provide quality customer service and ensure departmental and business goals are achieved.
“Proficiency in Portuguese is a must".

Should be flexible to do rotational shift: :24X7

Experience
  • Knowledge and proficiency using PC applications Excel, Word, Access and PowerPoint.
  • Graduate with minimum 1- 2 years of experience in similar field
Academic Background
  • Graduate with minimum 1- 2 years of experience in similar field
  • Familiarity with banking procedures and terminology
Functional Skills/Capabilities
  • Good analytical and problem-solving skills with close attention to detail.
  • Team player with the ability to collaborate with team members
  • Must be focused and self-motivated with the ability to work independently in a high volume, fast paced, and dynamic environment.
Technical Skills/Capabilities
  • Proficiency in Portuguese is a must.
  • Knowledge and proficiency using PC applications Excel, Word, Access and PowerPoint.
ReqID: 19015977
Schedule (Full-Time/Part-Time): Full-time

subject: Placement Coordinator Elections
body:
Greetings

This is to inform that elections for the post of placement coordinators
will be conducted on *Friday, 2 November 2018*.
Most probably, there will be a meeting of all the students with Prof.
Neelima Gupta prior to elections.
The timings of the elections will be informed soon ( tentatively 1 p.m. to
2:30 p.m. ).

Note :-

   - Everyone's attendance is mandatory.
   - Only the votes of the students who would have been physically present
   at the time of voting will be counted.
   - Proxies, voting via digital means ( like messages, calls ,etc ) or
   informing your classmates about your voting preferences won't be accepted.

Our Best Wishes to all !
Regards
*Placement Coordinators 2018-2019*

-- 
You received this message because you are subscribed to the Google Groups "DU MCS18" group.

organizing your projects and collaborating with your team in Trello. Here are 
our suggested next steps.

 You’re done 

⬜️ Add a card 
 Click “Add a card” to start adding tasks or ideas to your lists. Ready to go 
pro? Try dragging a card between lists. 

⬜️ Checklists 
 Add checklists to cards that require subtasks or multiple steps to make sure 
nothing falls through the cracks.

⬜️ Due Dates 
 Add a Due Date to cards with deadlines. Members of that card will receive a 
notification 24 hours before it’s due.

⬜️ Attachments 
 Add Attachments from both your computer, as well as cloud storage services 
like Dropbox, Google Drive, Box, and OneDrive.

subject: Peer Training Program - Web Development Workshop
body:
Google Forms


Thanks for filling out Peer Training Program - Web Development Workshop





Here's what we got from you:




Peer Training Program - Web Development Workshop


This workshop is intended for students who are interested in web  
development.

Duration: 4-5 hours

In this workshop, I will give a hands-on session on Modern PHP as the  
back-end for web development. I will be building up a little MVC  
application with modern PHP (using OOP concepts, autoloading, namespacing)  
without any dependencies. By the end of this session, I will give a short  
introduction to Laravel (a MVC framework for PHP webapps).

Here is the agenda of the workshop:

1. Introduction to PHP.
2. What is MVC?
3. How do websites work over the internet?
4. Hands-on Session.
5. Introduction to Laravel.
6. Other Popular Frameworks in different Languages.

Note: Since we have very limited space available, we can allow only 6  
students from each batch on the first-come first-served basis.


Email address *

megha.mcs18.du@gmail.com


Name *


Megha Sundriyal


Course/Batch *

M.Sc (II year)

body:
Explore our SQL Courses!

 

DataCamp ( https://www.datacamp.com )

 

 

-----------------------------------
SQL SELECT "Hello, world!";
-----------------------------------

Hi there,

Most of the world’s data lives in databases. To turn data into insights, you must know how to wrangle and extract it. SQL is the most popular and time-tested language to do this. Our SQL courses teach you everything you need to know to work with SQL.

Robert Chang, Data Scientist at Airbnb, puts it best: "If I want to pick one thing for all data scientists to learn, I would say learn SQL."

We’re excited to announce this expansion of our SQL curriculum. And we will be announcing many more SQL courses throughout the rest of the year.

subject: Srijan Curtain Call
body:
Greetings!



Hope you all are having a great time. It’s time to gear up for Sankalan
2019 and it is also the time to drop the curtain on the Srijan Panel
selections as well.



We are looking for a responsible, creative and dedicated team to lead and
work with us on this new edition of Srijan. If you are one of those who
looks for constructive recreation, Srijan is the right platform for you to
showcase your exemplary skills.



If anybody wants to send in his/her entry, you have time till *3rd February
2019* to do so. The selection process for the Srijan 2019 Panel is
explained in the attachment.

It is definitely a matter of pride to be on the Srijan Panel!

The Srijan Panel currently consists of 4 members:

*Editors -*

Jatin Rohilla - MCA 2nd year
( jatin.mca17.du@gmail.com )

Ashita Diwan - MSc. 2nd year
( ashita.mcs17.du@gmail.com )

*Designers -*

Vipin Kumar - MCA 2nd year
( vipin.mca17.du@gmail.com )

subject:
Fwd: New Delhi is having is Third Zoohackathon hosted by U.S.
 Embassy, WWF and TRAFFIC India - Welcome participation
body:
Dear All,
Pls find attached the information regarding Third Zoohackathon 2019 hosted
by U.S. Embassy, WWF and TRAFFIC India.
Kindly circulate this email among your classmates.
Students from the Department have earlier participated in this and other
hackathons, have gained knowledge and won appreciation.
There should be maximum participation from each class.
CRs - please compile the list of students who will be participating this
year and communicate the same to me.

Pls forward this email to MCA and MSc first year students as well.

Thanks,
Sapna Varshney
---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: vasudha bhatnagar <vasudhabhatnagar@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 1 Oct, 2019, 12:47 PM
Subject: Fwd: New Delhi is having is Third Zoohackathon hosted by U.S.
Embassy, WWF and TRAFFIC India - Welcome participation
To: Sapna Varshney <sapna.varsh@gmail.com>



Please circulate among students.
Let's encourage them.

Rgds

Vasudha Bhatnagar
Deptt. of Computer Science
University of Delhi, Delhi,  India.
Homepage: people.du.ac.in/~vbhatnagar/


---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: Ghose, Priya <GhoseP@state.gov>
Date: Tue, Oct 1, 2019 at 11:44 AM
Subject: New Delhi is having is Third Zoohackathon hosted by U.S. Embassy,
WWF and TRAFFIC India - Welcome participation
To: head@cs.du.ac.in <head@cs.du.ac.in>, vasudhabhatnagar@gmail.com <
vasudhabhatnagar@gmail.com>


Dear Dr. Bhatnagar:



The U.S. Embassy, WWF India and TRAFFIC India are hosting the third
Zoohackathon in New Delhi. The dates are November 16-17, 2019.



I am writing to request if this email can be circulated among your students
interested in participating.  A few students from your university had
participated previously as well and we welcome participation to this year’s
Zoohackathon.  The attached document has details of the Zoohackathon.
Please feel free to contact me if you need any more information.  I will
courier the Zoohackathon poster to you in the next few days.



*New Delhi is having is Third Zoohackathon!*



What is a Zoohackathon? It is a coding competition to develop
technology-focused solutions to address illegal wildlife trafficking and
create awareness



When:                   16-17 November, 2019.



Where:                 WWF India, 172 B, Lodi Road, New Delhi



Registration:      Registration will open from October 1, 2019.



Please read the attached sheet for more information.



*Please participate and inform your friends who may be interested in
participating. *



For more information please visit www.zoohackathon.com



With best wishes,



Priya Ghose

Environment Specialist

U.S. Embassy, New Delhi

Ph: 011 2419 8715





UNCLASSIFIED

subject: [Instr Note] Welcome to Piazza!
body:
Instructor Ronak Aggarwal posted a new Note. 

Welcome to Piazza!

Students,Welcome to Piazza! We'll be conducting all class-related discussion here this term. The quicker you begin asking questions on Piazza (rather than via emails), the quicker you'll benefit from the collective knowledge of your classmates and instructors. We encourage you to ask questions when you're struggling to understand a concept—you can even do so anonymously.-Ronak Aggarwal

Go to https://piazza.com/class?cid=jm4pyqh637d3q3&nid=jlyzzjfpkf861n&token=hndbUK7R05i to view. Search or link to this question with @6.  

Want Piazza in all your classes?  Tell your professors and TAs today.  It's free!

Thanks,
The Piazza Team
--
Contact us at team@piazza.com


You're receiving this email because megha.mcs18.du@gmail.com is enrolled in MCS 105 at University of Delhi. Go to https://piazza.com/login to sign in and manage your email preferences or proceed to https://piazza.com/remove/hndbUK7R05i/jlyzzjfpkf861n to un-enroll from this class.

subject: Registration for Deep Learning Workshop at 8:00 pm today :-)
body:
All the responses have been deleted.
Registration will start at 8:00 pm today.

On Fri, 22 Feb, 2019, 1:42 PM Sapna Varshney, <sapna.varsh@gmail.com> wrote:

> Hi All,
> Pls find below the link for registration form for Deep Learning Workshop.
> *The registrations will open at 8:00 pm today and close on 25th Feb 2019
> at 12:00 pm.*
>
> *https://goo.gl/forms/XAehIinTSiEqHxmc2
> <https://goo.gl/forms/XAehIinTSiEqHxmc2>*
>
> The students will be allowed on first-come-first-serve basis. Totals seats
> are 35 with 10 in waiting.
> *Students are required to bring their own laptop (64-bit) with
> Anaconda/Tensor Flow pre-installed for hands-on session.* Hardware and
> software installation instructions will be communicated soon. The hands-on
> session may be conducted online on Google platform.
>
> *Respective class CRs should send me a confirmation email on receipt of
> this email.*
>
> Thanks
> --
> Sapna Varshney
> Assistant Professor (Adhoc)
> Department of Computer Science
> University of Delhi, Delhi
>
